NewsMediaOrganization.name: NewsMediaOrganization
NewsMediaOrganization.help: A News/Media organization such as a newspaper or TV station.

inputs.name: actionableFeedbackPolicy
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroom’s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

inputs.name: correctionsPolicy
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroom’s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

inputs.name: diversityPolicy
inputs.help: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsroom’s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

inputs.name: diversityStaffingReport
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

inputs.name: ethicsPolicy
inputs.help: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

inputs.name: masthead
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a link to the masthead page or a page listing top editorial management.

inputs.name: missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement on coverage priorities, including any public agenda or stance on issues.

inputs.name: noBylinesPolicy
inputs.help: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement explaining when authors of articles are not named in bylines.

inputs.name: ownershipFundingInfo
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

inputs.name: unnamedSourcesPolicy
inputs.help: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

inputs.name: verificationFactCheckingPolicy
inputs.help: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

PlanAction.name: PlanAction
PlanAction.help: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.

inputs.name: scheduledTime
inputs.help: The time the object is scheduled to.

ListenAction.name: ListenAction
ListenAction.help: The act of consuming audio content.

TradeAction.name: TradeAction
TradeAction.help: The act of participating in an exchange of goods and services for monetary compensation. An agent trades an object, product or service with a participant in exchange for a one time or periodic payment.

inputs.name: price
inputs.help:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

inputs.name: priceCurrency
inputs.help: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: priceSpecification
inputs.help: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

PresentationDigitalDocument.name: PresentationDigitalDocument
PresentationDigitalDocument.help: A file containing slides or used for a presentation.

Reservation.name: Reservation
Reservation.help: Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets. \n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use [[Offer]].

inputs.name: bookingAgent
inputs.help: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

inputs.name: bookingTime
inputs.help: The date and time the reservation was booked.

inputs.name: broker
inputs.help: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

inputs.name: modifiedTime
inputs.help: The date and time the reservation was modified.

inputs.name: priceCurrency
inputs.help: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: programMembershipUsed
inputs.help: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

inputs.name: provider
inputs.help: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

inputs.name: reservationFor
inputs.help: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant,etc. being reserved.

inputs.name: reservationId
inputs.help: A unique identifier for the reservation.

inputs.name: reservationStatus
inputs.help: The current status of the reservation.

inputs.name: reservedTicket
inputs.help: A ticket associated with the reservation.

inputs.name: totalPrice
inputs.help:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

inputs.name: underName
inputs.help: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

AlignmentObject.name: AlignmentObject
AlignmentObject.help:
An intangible item that describes an alignment between a learning resource and a node in an educational framework.

Should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

inputs.name: alignmentType
inputs.help: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

inputs.name: educationalFramework
inputs.help: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

inputs.name: targetDescription
inputs.help: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

inputs.name: targetName
inputs.help: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

inputs.name: targetUrl
inputs.help: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

BedAndBreakfast.name: BedAndBreakfast
BedAndBreakfast.help:
Bed and breakfast.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

BusinessAudience.name: BusinessAudience
BusinessAudience.help: A set of characteristics belonging to businesses, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

inputs.name: numberOfEmployees
inputs.help: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

inputs.name: yearlyRevenue
inputs.help: The size of the business in annual revenue.

inputs.name: yearsInOperation
inputs.help: The age of the business.

JoinAction.name: JoinAction
JoinAction.help:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.

inputs.name: event
inputs.help: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

MedicalTest.name: MedicalTest
MedicalTest.help: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.

inputs.name: affectedBy
inputs.help: Drugs that affect the test's results.

inputs.name: normalRange
inputs.help: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

inputs.name: signDetected
inputs.help: A sign detected by the test.

inputs.name: usedToDiagnose
inputs.help: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

inputs.name: usesDevice
inputs.help: Device used to perform the test.

Person.name: Person
Person.help: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

inputs.name: additionalName
inputs.help: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

inputs.name: address
inputs.help: Physical address of the item.

inputs.name: affiliation
inputs.help: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

inputs.name: alumniOf
inputs.help: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

inputs.name: award
inputs.help: An award won by or for this item.

inputs.name: awards
inputs.help: Awards won by or for this item.

inputs.name: birthDate
inputs.help: Date of birth.

inputs.name: birthPlace
inputs.help: The place where the person was born.

inputs.name: brand
inputs.help: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

inputs.name: callSign
inputs.help: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

inputs.name: children
inputs.help: A child of the person.

inputs.name: colleague
inputs.help: A colleague of the person.

inputs.name: colleagues
inputs.help: A colleague of the person.

inputs.name: contactPoint
inputs.help: A contact point for a person or organization.

inputs.name: contactPoints
inputs.help: A contact point for a person or organization.

inputs.name: deathDate
inputs.help: Date of death.

inputs.name: deathPlace
inputs.help: The place where the person died.

inputs.name: duns
inputs.help: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

inputs.name: email
inputs.help: Email address.

inputs.name: familyName
inputs.help: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

inputs.name: faxNumber
inputs.help: The fax number.

inputs.name: follows
inputs.help: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

inputs.name: funder
inputs.help: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

inputs.name: gender
inputs.help: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While http://schema.org/Male and http://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

inputs.name: givenName
inputs.help: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

inputs.name: globalLocationNumber
inputs.help: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

inputs.name: hasCredential
inputs.help: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.

inputs.name: hasOccupation
inputs.help: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

inputs.name: hasOfferCatalog
inputs.help: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

inputs.name: hasPOS
inputs.help: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

inputs.name: height
inputs.help: The height of the item.

inputs.name: homeLocation
inputs.help: A contact location for a person's residence.

inputs.name: honorificPrefix
inputs.help: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

inputs.name: honorificSuffix
inputs.help: An honorific suffix following a Person's name such as M.D. /PhD/MSCSW.

inputs.name: interactionStatistic
inputs.help: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

inputs.name: isicV4
inputs.help: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

inputs.name: jobTitle
inputs.help: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

inputs.name: knows
inputs.help: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

inputs.name: knowsAbout
inputs.help: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.

inputs.name: knowsLanguage
inputs.help: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

inputs.name: makesOffer
inputs.help: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

inputs.name: memberOf
inputs.help: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

inputs.name: naics
inputs.help: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

inputs.name: nationality
inputs.help: Nationality of the person.

inputs.name: netWorth
inputs.help: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

inputs.name: owns
inputs.help: Products owned by the organization or person.

inputs.name: parent
inputs.help: A parent of this person.

inputs.name: parents
inputs.help: A parents of the person.

inputs.name: performerIn
inputs.help: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

inputs.name: publishingPrinciples
inputs.help:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

inputs.name: relatedTo
inputs.help: The most generic familial relation.

inputs.name: seeks
inputs.help: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

inputs.name: sibling
inputs.help: A sibling of the person.

inputs.name: siblings
inputs.help: A sibling of the person.

inputs.name: sponsor
inputs.help: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

inputs.name: spouse
inputs.help: The person's spouse.

inputs.name: taxID
inputs.help: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

inputs.name: telephone
inputs.help: The telephone number.

inputs.name: vatID
inputs.help: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

inputs.name: weight
inputs.help: The weight of the product or person.

inputs.name: workLocation
inputs.help: A contact location for a person's place of work.

inputs.name: worksFor
inputs.help: Organizations that the person works for.

MedicalCode.name: MedicalCode
MedicalCode.help: A code for a medical entity.

inputs.name: codeValue
inputs.help: A short textual code that uniquely identifies the value.

inputs.name: codingSystem
inputs.help: The coding system, e.g. 'ICD-10'.

Enumeration.name: Enumeration
Enumeration.help: Lists or enumerations—for example, a list of cuisines or music genres, etc.

inputs.name: supersededBy
inputs.help: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

CancelAction.name: CancelAction
CancelAction.help:
The act of asserting that a future event/action is no longer going to happen.

Related actions:

* [[ConfirmAction]]: The antonym of CancelAction.

AssignAction.name: AssignAction
AssignAction.help: The act of allocating an action/event/task to some destination (someone or something).

MediaReview.name: MediaReview
MediaReview.help:
A [[MediaReview]] is a more specialized form of Review dedicated to the evaluation of media content online, typically in the context of fact-checking and misinformation.
    For more general reviews of media in the broader sense, use [[UserReview]], [[CriticReview]] or other [[Review]] types. This definition is
    a work in progress. While the [[MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration]] list reflects significant community review amongst fact-checkers and others working
    to combat misinformation, the specific structures for representing media objects, their versions and publication context, is still evolving. Similarly, best practices for the relationship between [[MediaReview]] and [[ClaimReview]] markup has not yet been finalized.

inputs.name: mediaAuthenticityCategory
inputs.help: Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

inputs.name: originalMediaContextDescription
inputs.help: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

inputs.name: originalMediaLink
inputs.help: Link to the page containing an original version of the content, or directly to an online copy of the original [[MediaObject]] content, e.g. video file.

inputs.name: iataCode
inputs.help: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

inputs.name: icaoCode
inputs.help: ICAO identifier for an airport.

Quiz.name: Quiz
Quiz.help: Quiz: A test of knowledge, skills and abilities.

Order.name: Order
Order.help: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.

inputs.name: acceptedOffer
inputs.help: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

inputs.name: billingAddress
inputs.help: The billing address for the order.

inputs.name: broker
inputs.help: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

inputs.name: confirmationNumber
inputs.help: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

inputs.name: customer
inputs.help: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

inputs.name: discount
inputs.help: Any discount applied (to an Order).

inputs.name: discountCode
inputs.help: Code used to redeem a discount.

inputs.name: discountCurrency
inputs.help: The currency of the discount.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: isGift
inputs.help: Was the offer accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

inputs.name: merchant
inputs.help: 'merchant' is an out-dated term for 'seller'.

inputs.name: orderDate
inputs.help: Date order was placed.

inputs.name: orderDelivery
inputs.help: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

inputs.name: orderNumber
inputs.help: The identifier of the transaction.

inputs.name: orderStatus
inputs.help: The current status of the order.

inputs.name: orderedItem
inputs.help: The item ordered.

inputs.name: partOfInvoice
inputs.help: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

inputs.name: paymentDue
inputs.help: The date that payment is due.

inputs.name: paymentDueDate
inputs.help: The date that payment is due.

inputs.name: paymentMethod
inputs.help: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

inputs.name: paymentMethodId
inputs.help: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

inputs.name: paymentUrl
inputs.help: The URL for sending a payment.

inputs.name: seller
inputs.help: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

ChooseAction.name: ChooseAction
ChooseAction.help: The act of expressing a preference from a set of options or a large or unbounded set of choices/options.

inputs.name: actionOption
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

inputs.name: option
inputs.help: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

SomeProducts.name: SomeProducts
SomeProducts.help: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

inputs.name: inventoryLevel
inputs.help: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

GamePlayMode.name: GamePlayMode
GamePlayMode.help: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.

MediaReviewItem.name: MediaReviewItem
MediaReviewItem.help: Represents an item or group of closely related items treated as a unit for the sake of evaluation in a [[MediaReview]]. Authorship etc. apply to the items rather than to the curation/grouping or reviewing party.

inputs.name: mediaItemAppearance
inputs.help: In the context of a [[MediaReview]], indicates specific media item(s) that are grouped using a [[MediaReviewItem]].

LegalValueLevel.name: LegalValueLevel
LegalValueLevel.help: A list of possible levels for the legal validity of a legislation.

BookSeries.name: BookSeries
BookSeries.help: A series of books. Included books can be indicated with the hasPart property.

DrugCostCategory.name: DrugCostCategory
DrugCostCategory.help: Enumerated categories of medical drug costs.

inputs.name: acceptsReservations
inputs.help: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings ```Yes``` or ```No```.

inputs.name: hasMenu
inputs.help: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

inputs.name: menu
inputs.help: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

inputs.name: servesCuisine
inputs.help: The cuisine of the restaurant.

inputs.name: starRating
inputs.help: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

LendAction.name: LendAction
LendAction.help:
The act of providing an object under an agreement that it will be returned at a later date. Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

Related actions:

* [[BorrowAction]]: Reciprocal of LendAction.

inputs.name: borrower
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

DrugCost.name: DrugCost
DrugCost.help: The cost per unit of a medical drug. Note that this type is not meant to represent the price in an offer of a drug for sale; see the Offer type for that. This type will typically be used to tag wholesale or average retail cost of a drug, or maximum reimbursable cost. Costs of medical drugs vary widely depending on how and where they are paid for, so while this type captures some of the variables, costs should be used with caution by consumers of this schema's markup.

inputs.name: applicableLocation
inputs.help: The location in which the status applies.

inputs.name: costCategory
inputs.help: The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

inputs.name: costCurrency
inputs.help: The currency (in 3-letter of the drug cost. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217.

inputs.name: costOrigin
inputs.help: Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

inputs.name: costPerUnit
inputs.help: The cost per unit of the drug.

inputs.name: drugUnit
inputs.help: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

Demand.name: Demand
Demand.help: A demand entity represents the public, not necessarily binding, not necessarily exclusive, announcement by an organization or person to seek a certain type of goods or services. For describing demand using this type, the very same properties used for Offer apply.

inputs.name: acceptedPaymentMethod
inputs.help: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

inputs.name: advanceBookingRequirement
inputs.help: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

inputs.name: areaServed
inputs.help: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

inputs.name: availability
inputs.help: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

inputs.name: availabilityEnds
inputs.help: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

inputs.name: availabilityStarts
inputs.help: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

inputs.name: availableAtOrFrom
inputs.help: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

inputs.name: availableDeliveryMethod
inputs.help: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

inputs.name: businessFunction
inputs.help: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

inputs.name: deliveryLeadTime
inputs.help: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

inputs.name: eligibleCustomerType
inputs.help: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

inputs.name: eligibleDuration
inputs.help: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

inputs.name: eligibleQuantity
inputs.help: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

inputs.name: eligibleRegion
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: eligibleTransactionVolume
inputs.help: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

inputs.name: gtin
inputs.help: A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties. The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) express GTINs as URLs. A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged.

inputs.name: gtin12
inputs.help: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin13
inputs.help: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin14
inputs.help: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin8
inputs.help: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: includesObject
inputs.help: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

inputs.name: ineligibleRegion
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: inventoryLevel
inputs.help: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

inputs.name: itemCondition
inputs.help: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

inputs.name: itemOffered
inputs.help: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: mpn
inputs.help: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: priceSpecification
inputs.help: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

inputs.name: seller
inputs.help: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

inputs.name: serialNumber
inputs.help: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

inputs.name: sku
inputs.help: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validThrough
inputs.help: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

inputs.name: warranty
inputs.help: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

SportsActivityLocation.name: SportsActivityLocation
SportsActivityLocation.help: A sports location, such as a playing field.

UserReview.name: UserReview
UserReview.help: A review created by an end-user (e.g. consumer, purchaser, attendee etc.), in contrast with [[CriticReview]].

BusinessEntityType.name: BusinessEntityType
BusinessEntityType.help:
A business entity type is a conceptual entity representing the legal form, the size, the main line of business, the position in the value chain, or any combination thereof, of an organization or business person.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Business
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Enduser
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PublicInstitution
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Reseller

LocationFeatureSpecification.name: LocationFeatureSpecification
LocationFeatureSpecification.help: Specifies a location feature by providing a structured value representing a feature of an accommodation as a property-value pair of varying degrees of formality.

inputs.name: hoursAvailable
inputs.help: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validThrough
inputs.help: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

TherapeuticProcedure.name: TherapeuticProcedure
TherapeuticProcedure.help: A medical procedure intended primarily for therapeutic purposes, aimed at improving a health condition.

inputs.name: adverseOutcome
inputs.help: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or is otherwise life-threatening or requires immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriouseAdverseOutcome instead.

inputs.name: doseSchedule
inputs.help: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

inputs.name: drug
inputs.help: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

LegislativeBuilding.name: LegislativeBuilding
LegislativeBuilding.help: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.

WebPage.name: WebPage
WebPage.help: A web page. Every web page is implicitly assumed to be declared to be of type WebPage, so the various properties about that webpage, such as breadcrumb may be used. We recommend explicit declaration if these properties are specified, but if they are found outside of an itemscope, they will be assumed to be about the page.

inputs.name: breadcrumb
inputs.help: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

inputs.name: lastReviewed
inputs.help: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

inputs.name: mainContentOfPage
inputs.help: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

inputs.name: primaryImageOfPage
inputs.help: Indicates the main image on the page.

inputs.name: relatedLink
inputs.help: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

inputs.name: reviewedBy
inputs.help: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

inputs.name: significantLink
inputs.help: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

inputs.name: significantLinks
inputs.help: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

inputs.name: speakable
inputs.help:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.

2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, eg. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property.

3.)  XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property.


For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this
we define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]]  which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

inputs.name: specialty
inputs.help: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

Statement.name: Statement
Statement.help: A statement about something, for example a fun or interesting fact. If known, the main entity this statement is about, can be indicated using mainEntity. For more formal claims (e.g. in Fact Checking), consider using [[Claim]] instead. Use the [[text]] property to capture the text of the statement.

Clip.name: Clip
Clip.help: A short TV or radio program or a segment/part of a program.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: clipNumber
inputs.help: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

inputs.name: director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: endOffset
inputs.help: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: partOfEpisode
inputs.help: The episode to which this clip belongs.

inputs.name: partOfSeason
inputs.help: The season to which this episode belongs.

inputs.name: partOfSeries
inputs.help: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

inputs.name: startOffset
inputs.help: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

Room.name: Room
Room.help:
A room is a distinguishable space within a structure, usually separated from other spaces by interior walls. (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: characterAttribute
inputs.help: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

inputs.name: cheatCode
inputs.help: Cheat codes to the game.

inputs.name: containsSeason
inputs.help: A season that is part of the media series.

inputs.name: director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: episode
inputs.help: An episode of a tv, radio or game media within a series or season.

inputs.name: episodes
inputs.help: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

inputs.name: gameItem
inputs.help: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

inputs.name: gameLocation
inputs.help: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

inputs.name: gamePlatform
inputs.help: The electronic systems used to play video games.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: numberOfEpisodes
inputs.help: The number of episodes in this season or series.

inputs.name: numberOfPlayers
inputs.help: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

inputs.name: numberOfSeasons
inputs.help: The number of seasons in this series.

inputs.name: playMode
inputs.help: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

inputs.name: productionCompany
inputs.help: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

inputs.name: quest
inputs.help: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

inputs.name: season
inputs.help: A season in a media series.

inputs.name: seasons
inputs.help: A season in a media series.

inputs.name: trailer
inputs.help: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.

inputs.name: monthsOfExperience
inputs.help: Indicates the minimal number of months of experience required for a position.

MolecularEntity.name: MolecularEntity
MolecularEntity.help: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

inputs.name: chemicalRole
inputs.help: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a chemical context.

inputs.name: inChI
inputs.help: Non-proprietary identifier for molecular entity that can be used in printed and electronic data sources thus enabling easier linking of diverse data compilations.

inputs.name: inChIKey
inputs.help: InChIKey is a hashed version of the full InChI (using the SHA-256 algorithm).

inputs.name: iupacName
inputs.help: Systematic method of naming chemical compounds as recommended by the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC).

inputs.name: molecularFormula
inputs.help: The empirical formula is the simplest whole number ratio of all the atoms in a molecule.

inputs.name: molecularWeight
inputs.help: This is the molecular weight of the entity being described, not of the parent. Units should be included in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '12 amu' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

inputs.name: monoisotopicMolecularWeight
inputs.help: The monoisotopic mass is the sum of the masses of the atoms in a molecule using the unbound, ground-state, rest mass of the principal (most abundant) isotope for each element instead of the isotopic average mass. Please include the units the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '770.230488 g/mol' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

inputs.name: potentialUse
inputs.help: Intended use of the BioChemEntity by humans.

inputs.name: smiles
inputs.help: A specification in form of a line notation for describing the structure of chemical species using short ASCII strings.  Double bond stereochemistry \ indicators may need to be escaped in the string in formats where the backslash is an escape character.

ReturnMethodEnumeration.name: ReturnMethodEnumeration
ReturnMethodEnumeration.help: Enumerates several types of product return methods.

Residence.name: Residence
Residence.help: The place where a person lives.

inputs.name: accommodationFloorPlan
inputs.help: A floorplan of some [[Accommodation]].

Manuscript.name: Manuscript
Manuscript.help: A book, document, or piece of music written by hand rather than typed or printed.

SiteNavigationElement.name: SiteNavigationElement
SiteNavigationElement.help: A navigation element of the page.

SheetMusic.name: SheetMusic
SheetMusic.help: Printed music, as opposed to performed or recorded music.

DataType.name: DataType
DataType.help: The basic data types such as Integers, Strings, etc.

RadioEpisode.name: RadioEpisode
RadioEpisode.help: A radio episode which can be part of a series or season.

Season.name: Season
Season.help: A media season e.g. tv, radio, video game etc.

AnalysisNewsArticle.name: AnalysisNewsArticle
AnalysisNewsArticle.help: An AnalysisNewsArticle is a [[NewsArticle]] that, while based on factual reporting, incorporates the expertise of the author/producer, offering interpretations and conclusions.

Energy.name: Energy
Energy.help: Properties that take Energy as values are of the form '<Number> <Energy unit of measure>'.

DeactivateAction.name: DeactivateAction
DeactivateAction.help: The act of stopping or deactivating a device or application (e.g. stopping a timer or turning off a flashlight).

inputs.name: albumProductionType
inputs.help: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

inputs.name: albumRelease
inputs.help: A release of this album.

inputs.name: albumReleaseType
inputs.help: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

inputs.name: byArtist
inputs.help: The artist that performed this album or recording.

TravelAction.name: TravelAction
TravelAction.help: The act of traveling from an fromLocation to a destination by a specified mode of transport, optionally with participants.

inputs.name: distance
inputs.help: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

Permit.name: Permit
Permit.help: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.

inputs.name: issuedBy
inputs.help: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

inputs.name: issuedThrough
inputs.help: The service through with the permit was granted.

inputs.name: permitAudience
inputs.help: The target audience for this permit.

inputs.name: validFor
inputs.help: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validIn
inputs.help: The geographic area where a permit or similar thing is valid.

inputs.name: validUntil
inputs.help: The date when the item is no longer valid.

FundingScheme.name: FundingScheme
FundingScheme.help:
A FundingScheme combines organizational, project and policy aspects of grant-based funding
    that sets guidelines, principles and mechanisms to support other kinds of projects and activities.
    Funding is typically organized via [[Grant]] funding. Examples of funding schemes: Swiss Priority Programmes (SPPs); EU Framework 7 (FP7); Horizon 2020; the NIH-R01 Grant Program; Wellcome institutional strategic support fund. For large scale public sector funding, the management and administration of grant awards is often handled by other, dedicated, organizations - [[FundingAgency]]s such as ERC, REA, ...

Recommendation.name: Recommendation
Recommendation.help: [[Recommendation]] is a type of [[Review]] that suggests or proposes something as the best option or best course of action. Recommendations may be for products or services, or other concrete things, as in the case of a ranked list or product guide. A [[Guide]] may list multiple recommendations for different categories. For example, in a [[Guide]] about which TVs to buy, the author may have several [[Recommendation]]s.

inputs.name: category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

MarryAction.name: MarryAction
MarryAction.help: The act of marrying a person.

inputs.name: measurementTechnique
inputs.help:
A technique or technology used in a [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]),
corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using [[variableMeasured]]). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]].

BoatReservation.name: BoatReservation
BoatReservation.help:
A reservation for boat travel.

Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

Nerve.name: Nerve
Nerve.help: A common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons.

inputs.name: branch
inputs.help: The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with [[branchOf]].

inputs.name: nerveMotor
inputs.help: The neurological pathway extension that involves muscle control.

inputs.name: sensoryUnit
inputs.help: The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

inputs.name: sourcedFrom
inputs.help: The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

Question.name: Question
Question.help: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

inputs.name: acceptedAnswer
inputs.help: The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

inputs.name: answerCount
inputs.help: The number of answers this question has received.

inputs.name: eduQuestionType
inputs.help: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

inputs.name: suggestedAnswer
inputs.help: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

Substance.name: Substance
Substance.help: Any matter of defined composition that has discrete existence, whose origin may be biological, mineral or chemical.

inputs.name: activeIngredient
inputs.help: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

inputs.name: maximumIntake
inputs.help: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

Accommodation.name: Accommodation
Accommodation.help:
An accommodation is a place that can accommodate human beings, e.g. a hotel room, a camping pitch, or a meeting room. Many accommodations are for overnight stays, but this is not a mandatory requirement. For more specific types of accommodations not defined in schema.org, one can use additionalType with external vocabularies.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

inputs.name: accommodationCategory
inputs.help: Category of an [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions e.g. RESO (see [PropertySubType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertySubType+Field), and [PropertyType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertyType+Field) fields  for suggested values).

inputs.name: accommodationFloorPlan
inputs.help: A floorplan of some [[Accommodation]].

inputs.name: amenityFeature
inputs.help: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

inputs.name: floorLevel
inputs.help:
The floor level for an [[Accommodation]] in a multi-storey building. Since counting
  systems [vary internationally](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storey#Consecutive_number_floor_designations), the local system should be used where possible.

inputs.name: floorSize
inputs.help:
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.
Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard

inputs.name: leaseLength
inputs.help: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

inputs.name: numberOfBathroomsTotal
inputs.help: The total integer number of bathrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions as [documented in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsTotalInteger+Field): "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also [[numberOfRooms]].

inputs.name: numberOfBedrooms
inputs.help: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

inputs.name: numberOfFullBathrooms
inputs.help: Number of full bathrooms - The total number of full and ¾ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsFull field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsFull+Field).

inputs.name: numberOfPartialBathrooms
inputs.help: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and ¼ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

inputs.name: numberOfRooms
inputs.help:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

inputs.name: permittedUsage
inputs.help: Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

inputs.name: petsAllowed
inputs.help: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

inputs.name: tourBookingPage
inputs.help: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

inputs.name: yearBuilt
inputs.help: The year an [[Accommodation]] was constructed. This corresponds to the [YearBuilt field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/YearBuilt+Field).

Message.name: Message
Message.help: A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.

inputs.name: bccRecipient
inputs.help: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

inputs.name: ccRecipient
inputs.help: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

inputs.name: dateRead
inputs.help: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

inputs.name: dateReceived
inputs.help: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

inputs.name: dateSent
inputs.help: The date/time at which the message was sent.

inputs.name: messageAttachment
inputs.help: A CreativeWork attached to the message.

inputs.name: recipient
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

inputs.name: sender
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

inputs.name: toRecipient
inputs.help: A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

MedicalContraindication.name: MedicalContraindication
MedicalContraindication.help: A condition or factor that serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical therapy. Contraindications can be absolute (there are no reasonable circumstances for undertaking a course of action) or relative (the patient is at higher risk of complications, but that these risks may be outweighed by other considerations or mitigated by other measures).

MediaGallery.name: MediaGallery
MediaGallery.help: Web page type: Media gallery page. A mixed-media page that can contains media such as images, videos, and other multimedia.

RegisterAction.name: RegisterAction
RegisterAction.help:
The act of registering to be a user of a service, product or web page.

Related actions:

* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, RegisterAction implies you are registering to be a user of a service, *not* a group/team of people.
* [FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting to poll for updates from the object.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting updates from the object.

AmpStory.name: AmpStory
AmpStory.help: A creative work with a visual storytelling format intended to be viewed online, particularly on mobile devices.

ExercisePlan.name: ExercisePlan
ExercisePlan.help: Fitness-related activity designed for a specific health-related purpose, including defined exercise routines as well as activity prescribed by a clinician.

inputs.name: activityDuration
inputs.help: Length of time to engage in the activity.

inputs.name: activityFrequency
inputs.help: How often one should engage in the activity.

inputs.name: additionalVariable
inputs.help: Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.

inputs.name: exerciseType
inputs.help: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

inputs.name: intensity
inputs.help: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

inputs.name: repetitions
inputs.help: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

inputs.name: restPeriods
inputs.help: How often one should break from the activity.

inputs.name: workload
inputs.help: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration.name: MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration
MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration.help: Codes for use with the [[mediaAuthenticityCategory]] property, indicating the authenticity of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared). In general these codes are not mutually exclusive, although some combinations (such as 'original' versus 'transformed', 'edited' and 'staged') would be contradictory if applied in the same [[MediaReview]]. Note that the application of these codes is with regard to a piece of media shared or published in a particular context.

SendAction.name: SendAction
SendAction.help:
The act of physically/electronically dispatching an object for transfer from an origin to a destination.Related actions:

* [[ReceiveAction]]: The reciprocal of SendAction.
* [[GiveAction]]: Unlike GiveAction, SendAction does not imply the transfer of ownership (e.g. I can send you my laptop, but I'm not necessarily giving it to you).

inputs.name: deliveryMethod
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

inputs.name: recipient
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

Thesis.name: Thesis
Thesis.help: A thesis or dissertation document submitted in support of candidature for an academic degree or professional qualification.

inputs.name: inSupportOf
inputs.help: Qualification, candidature, degree, application that Thesis supports.

ShortStory.name: ShortStory
ShortStory.help: Short story or tale. A brief work of literature, usually written in narrative prose.

ScheduleAction.name: ScheduleAction
ScheduleAction.help:
Scheduling future actions, events, or tasks.

Related actions:

* [[ReserveAction]]: Unlike ReserveAction, ScheduleAction allocates future actions (e.g. an event, a task, etc) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

RadiationTherapy.name: RadiationTherapy
RadiationTherapy.help: A process of care using radiation aimed at improving a health condition.

EUEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration.name: EUEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration
EUEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration.help: Enumerates the EU energy efficiency classes A-G as well as A+, A++, and A+++ as defined in EU directive 2017/1369.

DiscoverAction.name: DiscoverAction
DiscoverAction.help: The act of discovering/finding an object.

RecommendedDoseSchedule.name: RecommendedDoseSchedule
RecommendedDoseSchedule.help: A recommended dosing schedule for a drug or supplement as prescribed or recommended by an authority or by the drug/supplement's manufacturer. Capture the recommending authority in the recognizingAuthority property of MedicalEntity.

MedicalSymptom.name: MedicalSymptom
MedicalSymptom.help: Any complaint sensed and expressed by the patient (therefore defined as subjective)  like stomachache, lower-back pain, or fatigue.

HealthAspectEnumeration.name: HealthAspectEnumeration
HealthAspectEnumeration.help: HealthAspectEnumeration enumerates several aspects of health content online, each of which might be described using [[hasHealthAspect]] and [[HealthTopicContent]].

MathSolver.name: MathSolver
MathSolver.help: A math solver which is capable of solving a subset of mathematical problems.

inputs.name: mathExpression
inputs.help: A mathematical expression (e.g. 'x^2-3x=0') that may be solved for a specific variable, simplified, or transformed. This can take many formats, e.g. LaTeX, Ascii-Math, or math as you would write with a keyboard.

MedicalSign.name: MedicalSign
MedicalSign.help: Any physical manifestation of a person's medical condition discoverable by objective diagnostic tests or physical examination.

inputs.name: identifyingExam
inputs.help: A physical examination that can identify this sign.

inputs.name: identifyingTest
inputs.help: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.

Mass.name: Mass
Mass.help: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'.

FinancialProduct.name: FinancialProduct
FinancialProduct.help: A product provided to consumers and businesses by financial institutions such as banks, insurance companies, brokerage firms, consumer finance companies, and investment companies which comprise the financial services industry.

inputs.name: annualPercentageRate
inputs.help: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

inputs.name: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
inputs.help: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

inputs.name: interestRate
inputs.help: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

inputs.name: applicationCategory
inputs.help: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

inputs.name: applicationSubCategory
inputs.help: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

inputs.name: applicationSuite
inputs.help: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

inputs.name: availableOnDevice
inputs.help: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

inputs.name: countriesNotSupported
inputs.help: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

inputs.name: countriesSupported
inputs.help: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

inputs.name: device
inputs.help: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

inputs.name: downloadUrl
inputs.help: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

inputs.name: featureList
inputs.help: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

inputs.name: fileSize
inputs.help: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

inputs.name: installUrl
inputs.help: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

inputs.name: memoryRequirements
inputs.help: Minimum memory requirements.

inputs.name: operatingSystem
inputs.help: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OSX 10.6, Android 1.6).

inputs.name: permissions
inputs.help: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

inputs.name: processorRequirements
inputs.help: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

inputs.name: releaseNotes
inputs.help: Description of what changed in this version.

inputs.name: requirements
inputs.help: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

inputs.name: screenshot
inputs.help: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

inputs.name: softwareAddOn
inputs.help: Additional content for a software application.

inputs.name: softwareHelp
inputs.help: Software application help.

inputs.name: softwareRequirements
inputs.help: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

inputs.name: softwareVersion
inputs.help: Version of the software instance.

inputs.name: storageRequirements
inputs.help: Storage requirements (free space required).

inputs.name: supportingData
inputs.help: Supporting data for a SoftwareApplication.

WearableSizeSystemEnumeration.name: WearableSizeSystemEnumeration
WearableSizeSystemEnumeration.help: Enumerates common size systems specific for wearable products

PalliativeProcedure.name: PalliativeProcedure
PalliativeProcedure.help: A medical procedure intended primarily for palliative purposes, aimed at relieving the symptoms of an underlying health condition.

TaxiReservation.name: TaxiReservation
TaxiReservation.help: A reservation for a taxi.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

inputs.name: partySize
inputs.help: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

inputs.name: pickupLocation
inputs.help: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

inputs.name: pickupTime
inputs.help: When a taxi will pickup a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

ComicCoverArt.name: ComicCoverArt
ComicCoverArt.help: The artwork on the cover of a comic.

ProductModel.name: ProductModel
ProductModel.help: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

inputs.name: isVariantOf
inputs.help: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of [[ProductModel]], this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a [[ProductGroup]], the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so it defines both a set of variants, as well as which values distinguish amongst those variants). When used with [[ProductGroup]], this property can apply to any [[Product]] included in the group.

inputs.name: predecessorOf
inputs.help: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

inputs.name: successorOf
inputs.help: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

DeliveryMethod.name: DeliveryMethod
DeliveryMethod.help:
A delivery method is a standardized procedure for transferring the product or service to the destination of fulfillment chosen by the customer. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the organization or group that is the contracting party for the sending organization or person.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeDirectDownload
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeFreight
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeMail
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeOwnFleet
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModePickUp
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

MerchantReturnPolicy.name: MerchantReturnPolicy
MerchantReturnPolicy.help: A MerchantReturnPolicy provides information about product return policies associated with an [[Organization]], [[Product]], or [[Offer]].

inputs.name: additionalProperty
inputs.help: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

inputs.name: customerRemorseReturnFees
inputs.help: The type of return fees if the product is returned due to customer remorse.

inputs.name: customerRemorseReturnLabelSource
inputs.help: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned due to customer remorse.

inputs.name: customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount
inputs.help: The amount of shipping costs if a product is returned due to customer remorse. Applicable when property [[customerRemorseReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

inputs.name: inStoreReturnsOffered
inputs.help: Are in-store returns offered? (for more advanced return methods use the [[returnMethod]] property)

inputs.name: itemCondition
inputs.help: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

inputs.name: itemDefectReturnFees
inputs.help: The type of return fees for returns of defect products.

inputs.name: itemDefectReturnLabelSource
inputs.help: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a defect product.

inputs.name: itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount
inputs.help: Amount of shipping costs for defect product returns. Applicable when property [[itemDefectReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

inputs.name: merchantReturnDays
inputs.help: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

inputs.name: merchantReturnLink
inputs.help: Specifies a Web page or service by URL, for product returns.

inputs.name: refundType
inputs.help: A refund type, from an enumerated list.

inputs.name: restockingFee
inputs.help: Use [[MonetaryAmount]] to specify a fixed restocking fee for product returns, or use [[Number]] to specify a percentage of the product price paid by the customer.

inputs.name: returnFees
inputs.help: The type of return fees for purchased products (for any return reason)

inputs.name: returnLabelSource
inputs.help: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned for any reason.

inputs.name: returnMethod
inputs.help: The type of return method offered, specified from an enumeration.

inputs.name: returnPolicyCategory
inputs.help: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

inputs.name: returnPolicyCountry
inputs.help: The country where the product has to be sent to for returns, for example "Ireland" using the [[name]] property of [[Country]]. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1). Note that this can be different from the country where the product was originally shipped from or sent too.

inputs.name: returnPolicySeasonalOverride
inputs.help: Seasonal override of a return policy.

inputs.name: returnShippingFeesAmount
inputs.help: Amount of shipping costs for product returns (for any reason). Applicable when property [[returnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

PropertyValue.name: PropertyValue
PropertyValue.help: A property-value pair, e.g. representing a feature of a product or place. Use the 'name' property for the name of the property. If there is an additional human-readable version of the value, put that into the 'description' property.\n\n Always use specific schema.org properties when a) they exist and b) you can populate them. Using PropertyValue as a substitute will typically not trigger the same effect as using the original, specific property.

inputs.name: maxValue
inputs.help: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: measurementTechnique
inputs.help:
A technique or technology used in a [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]),
corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using [[variableMeasured]]). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]].

inputs.name: minValue
inputs.help: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: propertyID
inputs.help:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific id of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).
Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

inputs.name: unitCode
inputs.help: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

inputs.name: unitText
inputs.help: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

inputs.name: value
inputs.help:
The value of the quantitative value or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
