Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin14
inputs.help: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin8
inputs.help: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: hasEnergyConsumptionDetails
inputs.help: Defines the energy efficiency Category (also known as "class" or "rating") for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

inputs.name: hasMeasurement
inputs.help: A product measurement, for example the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, or the gauge of a screw. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

inputs.name: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
inputs.help: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

inputs.name: height
inputs.help: The height of the item.

inputs.name: inProductGroupWithID
inputs.help: Indicates the [[productGroupID]] for a [[ProductGroup]] that this product [[isVariantOf]].

inputs.name: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
inputs.help: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

inputs.name: isConsumableFor
inputs.help: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

inputs.name: isRelatedTo
inputs.help: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

inputs.name: isSimilarTo
inputs.help: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

inputs.name: isVariantOf
inputs.help: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of [[ProductModel]], this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a [[ProductGroup]], the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so it defines both a set of variants, as well as which values distinguish amongst those variants). When used with [[ProductGroup]], this property can apply to any [[Product]] included in the group.

inputs.name: itemCondition
inputs.help: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

inputs.name: logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: manufacturer
inputs.help: The manufacturer of the product.

inputs.name: material
inputs.help: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

inputs.name: model
inputs.help: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

inputs.name: mpn
inputs.help: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: nsn
inputs.help: Indicates the [NATO stock number](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NATO_Stock_Number) (nsn) of a [[Product]].

inputs.name: offers
inputs.help: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: pattern
inputs.help: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

inputs.name: productID
inputs.help: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

inputs.name: productionDate
inputs.help: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

inputs.name: purchaseDate
inputs.help: The date the item e.g. vehicle was purchased by the current owner.

inputs.name: releaseDate
inputs.help: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

inputs.name: review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: reviews
inputs.help: Review of the item.

inputs.name: size
inputs.help: A standardized size of a product or creative work, specified either through a simple textual string (for example 'XL', '32Wx34L'), a  QuantitativeValue with a unitCode, or a comprehensive and structured [[SizeSpecification]]; in other cases, the [[width]], [[height]], [[depth]] and [[weight]] properties may be more applicable.

inputs.name: sku
inputs.help: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: slogan
inputs.help: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

inputs.name: weight
inputs.help: The weight of the product or person.

inputs.name: width
inputs.help: The width of the item.

ItemList.name: ItemList
ItemList.help: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.

inputs.name: itemListElement
inputs.help:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements.  Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

inputs.name: itemListOrder
inputs.help: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

inputs.name: numberOfItems
inputs.help: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

Resort.name: Resort
Resort.help:
A resort is a place used for relaxation or recreation, attracting visitors for holidays or vacations. Resorts are places, towns or sometimes commercial establishment operated by a single company (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

ControlAction.name: ControlAction
ControlAction.help: An agent controls a device or application.

InfectiousDisease.name: InfectiousDisease
InfectiousDisease.help: An infectious disease is a clinically evident human disease resulting from the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, like pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and prions. To be considered an infectious disease, such pathogens are known to be able to cause this disease.

inputs.name: infectiousAgent
inputs.help: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

inputs.name: infectiousAgentClass
inputs.help: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.

inputs.name: transmissionMethod
inputs.help: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

DateTime.name: DateTime
DateTime.help: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm] (see Chapter 5.4 of ISO 8601).

Rating.name: Rating
Rating.help: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

inputs.name: author
inputs.help: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

inputs.name: bestRating
inputs.help: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

inputs.name: ratingExplanation
inputs.help: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

inputs.name: ratingValue
inputs.help:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

inputs.name: reviewAspect
inputs.help: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

inputs.name: worstRating
inputs.help: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

PublicationEvent.name: PublicationEvent
PublicationEvent.help: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.

inputs.name: free
inputs.help: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

inputs.name: publishedBy
inputs.help: An agent associated with the publication event.

inputs.name: publishedOn
inputs.help: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

Brand.name: Brand
Brand.help: A brand is a name used by an organization or business person for labeling a product, product group, or similar.

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: slogan
inputs.help: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

StructuredValue.name: StructuredValue
StructuredValue.help: Structured values are used when the value of a property has a more complex structure than simply being a textual value or a reference to another thing.

BusReservation.name: BusReservation
BusReservation.help: A reservation for bus travel. \n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

CurrencyConversionService.name: CurrencyConversionService
CurrencyConversionService.help: A service to convert funds from one currency to another currency.

DisagreeAction.name: DisagreeAction
DisagreeAction.help: The act of expressing a difference of opinion with the object. An agent disagrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

DeliveryTimeSettings.name: DeliveryTimeSettings
DeliveryTimeSettings.help: A DeliveryTimeSettings represents re-usable pieces of shipping information, relating to timing. It is designed for publication on an URL that may be referenced via the [[shippingSettingsLink]] property of a [[OfferShippingDetails]]. Several occurrences can be published, distinguished (and identified/referenced) by their different values for [[transitTimeLabel]].

inputs.name: deliveryTime
inputs.help: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

inputs.name: isUnlabelledFallback
inputs.help: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

inputs.name: shippingDestination
inputs.help: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways e.g. postalCode ranges.

inputs.name: transitTimeLabel
inputs.help: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

WorkBasedProgram.name: WorkBasedProgram
WorkBasedProgram.help: A program with both an educational and employment component. Typically based at a workplace and structured around work-based learning, with the aim of instilling competencies related to an occupation. WorkBasedProgram is used to distinguish programs such as apprenticeships from school, college or other classroom based educational programs.

inputs.name: occupationalCategory
inputs.help:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

inputs.name: trainingSalary
inputs.help: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

InfectiousAgentClass.name: InfectiousAgentClass
InfectiousAgentClass.help: Classes of agents or pathogens that transmit infectious diseases. Enumerated type.

ExerciseAction.name: ExerciseAction
ExerciseAction.help: The act of participating in exertive activity for the purposes of improving health and fitness.

inputs.name: course
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

inputs.name: diet
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

inputs.name: distance
inputs.help: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

inputs.name: exerciseCourse
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

inputs.name: exercisePlan
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

inputs.name: exerciseRelatedDiet
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

inputs.name: exerciseType
inputs.help: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

inputs.name: fromLocation
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

inputs.name: opponent
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

inputs.name: sportsActivityLocation
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

inputs.name: sportsEvent
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

inputs.name: sportsTeam
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

inputs.name: toLocation
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

PhysicalTherapy.name: PhysicalTherapy
PhysicalTherapy.help: A process of progressive physical care and rehabilitation aimed at improving a health condition.

AdministrativeArea.name: AdministrativeArea
AdministrativeArea.help: A geographical region, typically under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

PrependAction.name: PrependAction
PrependAction.help: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.

CreateAction.name: CreateAction
CreateAction.help: The act of deliberately creating/producing/generating/building a result out of the agent.

inputs.name: numberOfRooms
inputs.help:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

inputs.name: occupancy
inputs.help:
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).
Typical unit code(s): C62 for person

Vehicle.name: Vehicle
Vehicle.help: A vehicle is a device that is designed or used to transport people or cargo over land, water, air, or through space.

inputs.name: accelerationTime
inputs.help:
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

* Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]], or use [[valueReference]] with a [[QuantitativeValue]] of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.

inputs.name: bodyType
inputs.help: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

inputs.name: callSign
inputs.help: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

inputs.name: cargoVolume
inputs.help:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.

Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet

Note: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

inputs.name: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
inputs.help: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

inputs.name: driveWheelConfiguration
inputs.help: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

inputs.name: emissionsCO2
inputs.help: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

inputs.name: fuelCapacity
inputs.help: The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.\n\nTypical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

inputs.name: fuelConsumption
inputs.help:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km.  Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

inputs.name: fuelEfficiency
inputs.help:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

inputs.name: fuelType
inputs.help: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

inputs.name: knownVehicleDamages
inputs.help: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

inputs.name: meetsEmissionStandard
inputs.help: Indicates that the vehicle meets the respective emission standard.

inputs.name: mileageFromOdometer
inputs.help: The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.\n\nTypical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles

inputs.name: modelDate
inputs.help: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

inputs.name: numberOfAirbags
inputs.help: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

inputs.name: numberOfAxles
inputs.help: The number of axles.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

inputs.name: numberOfDoors
inputs.help: The number of doors.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

inputs.name: numberOfForwardGears
inputs.help: The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

inputs.name: numberOfPreviousOwners
inputs.help: The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

inputs.name: payload
inputs.help:
The permitted weight of passengers and cargo, EXCLUDING the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: Many databases specify the permitted TOTAL weight instead, which is the sum of [[weight]] and [[payload]]
* Note 2: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 3: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 4: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

inputs.name: productionDate
inputs.help: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

inputs.name: purchaseDate
inputs.help: The date the item e.g. vehicle was purchased by the current owner.

inputs.name: seatingCapacity
inputs.help: The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons

inputs.name: speed
inputs.help:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]] should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.

inputs.name: steeringPosition
inputs.help: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

inputs.name: tongueWeight
inputs.help:
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR)

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

inputs.name: trailerWeight
inputs.help:
The permitted weight of a trailer attached to the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound
* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

inputs.name: vehicleConfiguration
inputs.help: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

inputs.name: vehicleEngine
inputs.help: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

inputs.name: vehicleIdentificationNumber
inputs.help: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

inputs.name: vehicleInteriorColor
inputs.help: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

inputs.name: vehicleInteriorType
inputs.help: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

inputs.name: vehicleModelDate
inputs.help: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

inputs.name: vehicleSeatingCapacity
inputs.help: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

inputs.name: vehicleSpecialUsage
inputs.help: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

inputs.name: vehicleTransmission
inputs.help: The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) ("gearbox" for cars).

inputs.name: weightTotal
inputs.help:
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

inputs.name: wheelbase
inputs.help: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.\n\nTypical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet

WearableSizeGroupEnumeration.name: WearableSizeGroupEnumeration
WearableSizeGroupEnumeration.help: Enumerates common size groups (also known as "size types") for wearable products.

FlightReservation.name: FlightReservation
FlightReservation.help: A reservation for air travel.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

inputs.name: boardingGroup
inputs.help: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

inputs.name: passengerPriorityStatus
inputs.help: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

inputs.name: passengerSequenceNumber
inputs.help: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

inputs.name: securityScreening
inputs.help: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

AppendAction.name: AppendAction
AppendAction.help: The act of inserting at the end if an ordered collection.

inputs.name: availableService
inputs.help: A medical service available from this provider.

inputs.name: hospitalAffiliation
inputs.help: A hospital with which the physician or office is affiliated.

inputs.name: medicalSpecialty
inputs.help: A medical specialty of the provider.

MonetaryAmountDistribution.name: MonetaryAmountDistribution
MonetaryAmountDistribution.help: A statistical distribution of monetary amounts.

inputs.name: currency
inputs.help: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

MeetingRoom.name: MeetingRoom
MeetingRoom.help:
A meeting room, conference room, or conference hall is a room provided for singular events such as business conferences and meetings (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_hall).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

Quantity.name: Quantity
Quantity.help: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 Kg' or '4 milligrams'.

EventStatusType.name: EventStatusType
EventStatusType.help: EventStatusType is an enumeration type whose instances represent several states that an Event may be in.

ArchiveComponent.name: ArchiveComponent
ArchiveComponent.help: An intangible type to be applied to any archive content, carrying with it a set of properties required to describe archival items and collections.

inputs.name: holdingArchive
inputs.help: [[ArchiveOrganization]] that holds, keeps or maintains the [[ArchiveComponent]].

inputs.name: itemLocation
inputs.help: Current location of the item.

EnergyConsumptionDetails.name: EnergyConsumptionDetails
EnergyConsumptionDetails.help: EnergyConsumptionDetails represents information related to the energy efficiency of a product that consumes energy. The information that can be provided is based on international regulations such as for example [EU directive 2017/1369](https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2017/1369/oj) for energy labeling and the [Energy labeling rule](https://www.ftc.gov/enforcement/rules/rulemaking-regulatory-reform-proceedings/energy-water-use-labeling-consumer) under the Energy Policy and Conservation Act (EPCA) in the US.

inputs.name: energyEfficiencyScaleMax
inputs.help: Specifies the most energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

inputs.name: energyEfficiencyScaleMin
inputs.help: Specifies the least energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

inputs.name: hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory
inputs.help: Defines the energy efficiency Category (which could be either a rating out of range of values or a yes/no certification) for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

EducationalOccupationalCredential.name: EducationalOccupationalCredential
EducationalOccupationalCredential.help: An educational or occupational credential. A diploma, academic degree, certification, qualification, badge, etc., that may be awarded to a person or other entity that meets the requirements defined by the credentialer.

inputs.name: competencyRequired
inputs.help: Knowledge, skill, ability or personal attribute that must be demonstrated by a person or other entity in order to do something such as earn an Educational Occupational Credential or understand a LearningResource.

inputs.name: credentialCategory
inputs.help: The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree”, “certificate”, “badge”, or more specific term.

inputs.name: educationalLevel
inputs.help: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

inputs.name: recognizedBy
inputs.help: An organization that acknowledges the validity, value or utility of a credential. Note: recognition may include a process of quality assurance or accreditation.

inputs.name: validFor
inputs.help: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

inputs.name: validIn
inputs.help: The geographic area where a permit or similar thing is valid.

FindAction.name: FindAction
FindAction.help:
The act of finding an object.

Related actions:

* [[SearchAction]]: FindAction is generally lead by a SearchAction, but not necessarily.

OfferForLease.name: OfferForLease
OfferForLease.help:
An [[OfferForLease]] in Schema.org represents an [[Offer]] to lease out something, i.e. an [[Offer]] whose
  [[businessFunction]] is [lease out](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#LeaseOut.). See [Good Relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoodRelations) for
  background on the underlying concepts.

TipAction.name: TipAction
TipAction.help: The act of giving money voluntarily to a beneficiary in recognition of services rendered.

inputs.name: recipient
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

AskAction.name: AskAction
AskAction.help:
The act of posing a question / favor to someone.

Related actions:

* [[ReplyAction]]: Appears generally as a response to AskAction.

inputs.name: question
inputs.help: A sub property of object. A question.

HVACBusiness.name: HVACBusiness
HVACBusiness.help: A business that provide Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning services.

RadioSeries.name: RadioSeries
RadioSeries.help: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: containsSeason
inputs.help: A season that is part of the media series.

inputs.name: director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: episode
inputs.help: An episode of a tv, radio or game media within a series or season.

inputs.name: episodes
inputs.help: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: numberOfEpisodes
inputs.help: The number of episodes in this season or series.

inputs.name: numberOfSeasons
inputs.help: The number of seasons in this series.

inputs.name: productionCompany
inputs.help: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

inputs.name: season
inputs.help: A season in a media series.

inputs.name: seasons
inputs.help: A season in a media series.

inputs.name: trailer
inputs.help: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.

TreatmentIndication.name: TreatmentIndication
TreatmentIndication.help: An indication for treating an underlying condition, symptom, etc.

TrainTrip.name: TrainTrip
TrainTrip.help: A trip on a commercial train line.

inputs.name: arrivalPlatform
inputs.help: The platform where the train arrives.

inputs.name: arrivalStation
inputs.help: The station where the train trip ends.

inputs.name: departurePlatform
inputs.help: The platform from which the train departs.

inputs.name: departureStation
inputs.help: The station from which the train departs.

inputs.name: trainName
inputs.help: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

inputs.name: trainNumber
inputs.help: The unique identifier for the train.

JobPosting.name: JobPosting
JobPosting.help: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.

inputs.name: applicantLocationRequirements
inputs.help: The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

inputs.name: applicationContact
inputs.help: Contact details for further information relevant to this job posting.

inputs.name: baseSalary
inputs.help: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

inputs.name: benefits
inputs.help: Description of benefits associated with the job.

inputs.name: datePosted
inputs.help: Publication date of an online listing.

inputs.name: directApply
inputs.help: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specified job, navigating directly from the JobPosting url(s) supplied.

inputs.name: educationRequirements
inputs.help: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

inputs.name: eligibilityToWorkRequirement
inputs.help: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

inputs.name: employerOverview
inputs.help: A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

inputs.name: employmentType
inputs.help: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

inputs.name: employmentUnit
inputs.help: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

inputs.name: estimatedSalary
inputs.help: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

inputs.name: experienceInPlaceOfEducation
inputs.help: Indicates whether a [[JobPosting]] will accept experience (as indicated by [[OccupationalExperienceRequirements]]) in place of its formal educational qualifications (as indicated by [[educationRequirements]]). If true, indicates that satisfying one of these requirements is sufficient.

inputs.name: experienceRequirements
inputs.help: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

inputs.name: hiringOrganization
inputs.help: Organization offering the job position.

inputs.name: incentiveCompensation
inputs.help: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

inputs.name: incentives
inputs.help: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

inputs.name: industry
inputs.help: The industry associated with the job position.

inputs.name: jobBenefits
inputs.help: Description of benefits associated with the job.

inputs.name: jobImmediateStart
inputs.help: An indicator as to whether a position is available for an immediate start.

inputs.name: jobLocation
inputs.help: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

inputs.name: jobLocationType
inputs.help: A description of the job location (e.g TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

inputs.name: jobStartDate
inputs.help: The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

inputs.name: occupationalCategory
inputs.help:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

inputs.name: physicalRequirement
inputs.help: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

inputs.name: qualifications
inputs.help: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

inputs.name: relevantOccupation
inputs.help: The Occupation for the JobPosting.

inputs.name: responsibilities
inputs.help: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

inputs.name: salaryCurrency
inputs.help: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) ) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

inputs.name: securityClearanceRequirement
inputs.help: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

inputs.name: sensoryRequirement
inputs.help: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

inputs.name: skills
inputs.help: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is desired or required to fulfill this role or to work in this occupation.

inputs.name: specialCommitments
inputs.help: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

inputs.name: title
inputs.help: The title of the job.

inputs.name: totalJobOpenings
inputs.help: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

inputs.name: validThrough
inputs.help: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

inputs.name: workHours
inputs.help: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

PlayAction.name: PlayAction
PlayAction.help:
The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, Competition or exercise.

Related actions:

* [[ListenAction]]: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.
* [[WatchAction]]: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content.

inputs.name: audience
inputs.help: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

inputs.name: event
inputs.help: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

Collection.name: Collection
Collection.help: A collection of items e.g. creative works or products.

inputs.name: collectionSize
inputs.help: The number of items in the [[Collection]].

MoveAction.name: MoveAction
MoveAction.help:
The act of an agent relocating to a place.

Related actions:

* [[TransferAction]]: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.

inputs.name: fromLocation
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

inputs.name: toLocation
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

MiddleSchool.name: MiddleSchool
MiddleSchool.help: A middle school (typically for children aged around 11-14, although this varies somewhat).

PostalCodeRangeSpecification.name: PostalCodeRangeSpecification
PostalCodeRangeSpecification.help: Indicates a range of postalcodes, usually defined as the set of valid codes between [[postalCodeBegin]] and [[postalCodeEnd]], inclusively.

inputs.name: postalCodeBegin
inputs.help: First postal code in a range (included).

inputs.name: postalCodeEnd
inputs.help: Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after [[postalCodeBegin]].

EmployerAggregateRating.name: EmployerAggregateRating
EmployerAggregateRating.help: An aggregate rating of an Organization related to its role as an employer.

Ticket.name: Ticket
Ticket.help: Used to describe a ticket to an event, a flight, a bus ride, etc.

inputs.name: dateIssued
inputs.help: The date the ticket was issued.

inputs.name: issuedBy
inputs.help: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

inputs.name: priceCurrency
inputs.help: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: ticketNumber
inputs.help: The unique identifier for the ticket.

inputs.name: ticketToken
inputs.help: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

inputs.name: ticketedSeat
inputs.help: The seat associated with the ticket.

inputs.name: totalPrice
inputs.help:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

inputs.name: underName
inputs.help: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

BroadcastFrequencySpecification.name: BroadcastFrequencySpecification
BroadcastFrequencySpecification.help: The frequency in MHz and the modulation used for a particular BroadcastService.

inputs.name: broadcastFrequencyValue
inputs.help: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

inputs.name: broadcastSignalModulation
inputs.help: The modulation (e.g. FM, AM, etc) used by a particular broadcast service.

inputs.name: broadcastSubChannel
inputs.help: The subchannel used for the broadcast.

Series.name: Series
Series.help: A Series in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. See also [[CreativeWorkSeries]], [[EventSeries]].

WinAction.name: WinAction
WinAction.help: The act of achieving victory in a competitive activity.

inputs.name: loser
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

SatiricalArticle.name: SatiricalArticle
SatiricalArticle.help: An [[Article]] whose content is primarily [[satirical]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satire) in nature, i.e. unlikely to be literally true. A satirical article is sometimes but not necessarily also a [[NewsArticle]]. [[ScholarlyArticle]]s are also sometimes satirized.

inputs.name: abridged
inputs.help: Indicates whether the book is an abridged edition.

inputs.name: bookEdition
inputs.help: The edition of the book.

inputs.name: bookFormat
inputs.help: The format of the book.

inputs.name: illustrator
inputs.help: The illustrator of the book.

inputs.name: isbn
inputs.help: The ISBN of the book.

inputs.name: numberOfPages
inputs.help: The number of pages in the book.

BloodTest.name: BloodTest
BloodTest.help: A medical test performed on a sample of a patient's blood.

InsertAction.name: InsertAction
InsertAction.help: The act of adding at a specific location in an ordered collection.

inputs.name: toLocation
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

Occupation.name: Occupation
Occupation.help: A profession, may involve prolonged training and/or a formal qualification.

inputs.name: educationRequirements
inputs.help: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

inputs.name: estimatedSalary
inputs.help: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

inputs.name: experienceRequirements
inputs.help: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

inputs.name: occupationLocation
inputs.help: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

inputs.name: occupationalCategory
inputs.help:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

inputs.name: qualifications
inputs.help: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

inputs.name: responsibilities
inputs.help: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

inputs.name: skills
inputs.help: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is desired or required to fulfill this role or to work in this occupation.

Optician.name: Optician
Optician.help: A store that sells reading glasses and similar devices for improving vision.

GovernmentOffice.name: GovernmentOffice
GovernmentOffice.help: A government office—for example, an IRS or DMV office.

LodgingBusiness.name: LodgingBusiness
LodgingBusiness.help: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.

inputs.name: amenityFeature
inputs.help: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

inputs.name: audience
inputs.help: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

inputs.name: availableLanguage
inputs.help: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]]

inputs.name: checkinTime
inputs.help: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

inputs.name: checkoutTime
inputs.help: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

inputs.name: numberOfRooms
inputs.help:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

inputs.name: petsAllowed
inputs.help: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

inputs.name: starRating
inputs.help: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

DownloadAction.name: DownloadAction
DownloadAction.help: The act of downloading an object.

SteeringPositionValue.name: SteeringPositionValue
SteeringPositionValue.help: A value indicating a steering position.

AcceptAction.name: AcceptAction
AcceptAction.help:
The act of committing to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

* [[RejectAction]]: The antonym of AcceptAction.

Grant.name: Grant
Grant.help:
A grant, typically financial or otherwise quantifiable, of resources. Typically a [[funder]] sponsors some [[MonetaryAmount]] to an [[Organization]] or [[Person]],
    sometimes not necessarily via a dedicated or long-lived [[Project]], resulting in one or more outputs, or [[fundedItem]]s. For financial sponsorship, indicate the [[funder]] of a [[MonetaryGrant]]. For non-financial support, indicate [[sponsor]] of [[Grant]]s of resources (e.g. office space).

Grants support  activities directed towards some agreed collective goals, often but not always organized as [[Project]]s. Long-lived projects are sometimes sponsored by a variety of grants over time, but it is also common for a project to be associated with a single grant.

The amount of a [[Grant]] is represented using [[amount]] as a [[MonetaryAmount]].

inputs.name: fundedItem
inputs.help: Indicates an item funded or sponsored through a [[Grant]].

inputs.name: sponsor
inputs.help: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

UserPlays.name: UserPlays
UserPlays.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

MedicalAudienceType.name: MedicalAudienceType
MedicalAudienceType.help: Target audiences types for medical web pages. Enumerated type.

MedicalStudyStatus.name: MedicalStudyStatus
MedicalStudyStatus.help: The status of a medical study. Enumerated type.

Drug.name: Drug
Drug.help: A chemical or biologic substance, used as a medical therapy, that has a physiological effect on an organism. Here the term drug is used interchangeably with the term medicine although clinical knowledge make a clear difference between them.

inputs.name: activeIngredient
inputs.help: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

inputs.name: administrationRoute
inputs.help: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

inputs.name: alcoholWarning
inputs.help: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

inputs.name: availableStrength
inputs.help: An available dosage strength for the drug.

inputs.name: breastfeedingWarning
inputs.help: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

inputs.name: clincalPharmacology
inputs.help: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

inputs.name: clinicalPharmacology
inputs.help: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

inputs.name: dosageForm
inputs.help: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

inputs.name: doseSchedule
inputs.help: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

inputs.name: drugClass
inputs.help: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

inputs.name: drugUnit
inputs.help: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

inputs.name: foodWarning
inputs.help: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.

inputs.name: includedInHealthInsurancePlan
inputs.help: The insurance plans that cover this drug.

inputs.name: interactingDrug
inputs.help: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

inputs.name: isAvailableGenerically
inputs.help: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

inputs.name: isProprietary
inputs.help: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

inputs.name: labelDetails
inputs.help: Link to the drug's label details.

inputs.name: legalStatus
inputs.help: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

inputs.name: manufacturer
inputs.help: The manufacturer of the product.

inputs.name: maximumIntake
inputs.help: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

inputs.name: mechanismOfAction
inputs.help: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

inputs.name: nonProprietaryName
inputs.help: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

inputs.name: overdosage
inputs.help: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

inputs.name: pregnancyCategory
inputs.help: Pregnancy category of this drug.

inputs.name: pregnancyWarning
inputs.help: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

inputs.name: prescribingInfo
inputs.help: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

inputs.name: prescriptionStatus
inputs.help: Indicates the status of drug prescription eg. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

inputs.name: proprietaryName
inputs.help: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

inputs.name: relatedDrug
inputs.help: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

inputs.name: rxcui
inputs.help: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

inputs.name: warning
inputs.help: Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

SurgicalProcedure.name: SurgicalProcedure
SurgicalProcedure.help: A medical procedure involving an incision with instruments; performed for diagnose, or therapeutic purposes.

TheaterGroup.name: TheaterGroup
TheaterGroup.help: A theater group or company, for example, the Royal Shakespeare Company or Druid Theatre.

PaymentService.name: PaymentService
PaymentService.help: A Service to transfer funds from a person or organization to a beneficiary person or organization.

inputs.name: browserRequirements
inputs.help: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

InteractionCounter.name: InteractionCounter
InteractionCounter.help: A summary of how users have interacted with this CreativeWork. In most cases, authors will use a subtype to specify the specific type of interaction.

inputs.name: endTime
inputs.help: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

inputs.name: interactionService
inputs.help: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

inputs.name: interactionType
inputs.help: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use [[LikeAction]]. For down votes use [[DislikeAction]]. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

inputs.name: location
inputs.help: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

inputs.name: startTime
inputs.help: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

inputs.name: userInteractionCount
inputs.help: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

ReviewAction.name: ReviewAction
ReviewAction.help: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.

inputs.name: resultReview
inputs.help: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

MedicalEntity.name: MedicalEntity
MedicalEntity.help: The most generic type of entity related to health and the practice of medicine.

inputs.name: code
inputs.help: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

inputs.name: guideline
inputs.help: A medical guideline related to this entity.

inputs.name: legalStatus
inputs.help: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

inputs.name: medicineSystem
inputs.help: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

inputs.name: recognizingAuthority
inputs.help: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

inputs.name: relevantSpecialty
inputs.help: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

inputs.name: study
inputs.help: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

BrainStructure.name: BrainStructure
BrainStructure.help: Any anatomical structure which pertains to the soft nervous tissue functioning as the coordinating center of sensation and intellectual and nervous activity.

SellAction.name: SellAction
SellAction.help: The act of taking money from a buyer in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent sells an object, product, or service to a buyer for a price. Reciprocal of BuyAction.

inputs.name: buyer
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

inputs.name: warrantyPromise
inputs.help: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

inputs.name: duration
inputs.help: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: readBy
inputs.help: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

CheckOutAction.name: CheckOutAction
CheckOutAction.help:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their departure of a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check in) or place (e.g. hotel).

Related actions:

* [[CheckInAction]]: The antonym of CheckOutAction.
* [[DepartAction]]: Unlike DepartAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service.
* [[CancelAction]]: Unlike CancelAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service.

UnitPriceSpecification.name: UnitPriceSpecification
UnitPriceSpecification.help: The price asked for a given offer by the respective organization or person.

inputs.name: billingDuration
inputs.help: Specifies for how long this price (or price component) will be billed. Can be used, for example, to model the contractual duration of a subscription or payment plan. Type can be either a Duration or a Number (in which case the unit of measurement, for example month, is specified by the unitCode property).

inputs.name: billingIncrement
inputs.help: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

inputs.name: billingStart
inputs.help: Specifies after how much time this price (or price component) becomes valid and billing starts. Can be used, for example, to model a price increase after the first year of a subscription. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

inputs.name: priceComponentType
inputs.help: Identifies a price component (for example, a line item on an invoice), part of the total price for an offer.

inputs.name: priceType
inputs.help: Defines the type of a price specified for an offered product, for example a list price, a (temporary) sale price or a manufacturer suggested retail price. If multiple prices are specified for an offer the [[priceType]] property can be used to identify the type of each such specified price. The value of priceType can be specified as a value from enumeration PriceTypeEnumeration or as a free form text string for price types that are not already predefined in PriceTypeEnumeration.

inputs.name: referenceQuantity
inputs.help: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

inputs.name: unitCode
inputs.help: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

inputs.name: unitText
inputs.help: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

BoatTrip.name: BoatTrip
BoatTrip.help: A trip on a commercial ferry line.

inputs.name: arrivalBoatTerminal
inputs.help: The terminal or port from which the boat arrives.

inputs.name: departureBoatTerminal
inputs.help: The terminal or port from which the boat departs.

OfferShippingDetails.name: OfferShippingDetails
OfferShippingDetails.help:
OfferShippingDetails represents information about shipping destinations.

Multiple of these entities can be used to represent different shipping rates for different destinations:

One entity for Alaska/Hawaii. A different one for continental US.A different one for all France.

Multiple of these entities can be used to represent different shipping costs and delivery times.

Two entities that are identical but differ in rate and time:

e.g. Cheaper and slower: $5 in 5-7days
or Fast and expensive: $15 in 1-2 days.

inputs.name: deliveryTime
inputs.help: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

inputs.name: doesNotShip
inputs.help: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

inputs.name: shippingDestination
inputs.help: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways e.g. postalCode ranges.

inputs.name: shippingLabel
inputs.help: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[ShippingRateSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

inputs.name: shippingRate
inputs.help: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

inputs.name: shippingSettingsLink
inputs.help: Link to a page containing [[ShippingRateSettings]] and [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] details.

inputs.name: transitTimeLabel
inputs.help: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

MenuItem.name: MenuItem
MenuItem.help: A food or drink item listed in a menu or menu section.

inputs.name: menuAddOn
inputs.help: Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

inputs.name: nutrition
inputs.help: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

inputs.name: offers
inputs.help: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: suitableForDiet
inputs.help: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

Protein.name: Protein
Protein.help: Protein is here used in its widest possible definition, as classes of amino acid based molecules. Amyloid-beta Protein in human (UniProt P05067), eukaryota (e.g. an OrthoDB group) or even a single molecule that one can point to are all of type schema:Protein. A protein can thus be a subclass of another protein, e.g. schema:Protein as a UniProt record can have multiple isoforms inside it which would also be schema:Protein. They can be imagined, synthetic, hypothetical or naturally occurring.

inputs.name: hasBioPolymerSequence
inputs.help: A symbolic representation of a BioChemEnity. For example, a nucleotide sequence of a Gene or an amino acid sequence of a Protein.

WantAction.name: WantAction
WantAction.help: The act of expressing a desire about the object. An agent wants an object.

HyperToc.name: HyperToc
HyperToc.help: A HyperToc represents a hypertext table of contents for complex media objects, such as [[VideoObject]], [[AudioObject]]. Items in the table of contents are indicated using the [[tocEntry]] property, and typed [[HyperTocEntry]]. For cases where the same larger work is split into multiple files, [[associatedMedia]] can be used on individual [[HyperTocEntry]] items.

inputs.name: associatedMedia
inputs.help: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

inputs.name: tocEntry
inputs.help: Indicates a [[HyperTocEntry]] in a [[HyperToc]].

TrackAction.name: TrackAction
TrackAction.help:
An agent tracks an object for updates.

Related actions:

* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimates objects.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, TrackAction refers to  the interest on the location of innanimate objects.

inputs.name: deliveryMethod
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

DrugPregnancyCategory.name: DrugPregnancyCategory
DrugPregnancyCategory.help: Categories that represent an assessment of the risk of fetal injury due to a drug or pharmaceutical used as directed by the mother during pregnancy.

MusicPlaylist.name: MusicPlaylist
MusicPlaylist.help: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.

inputs.name: numTracks
inputs.help: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

inputs.name: track
inputs.help: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

inputs.name: tracks
inputs.help: A music recording (track)—usually a single song.

EmergencyService.name: EmergencyService
EmergencyService.help: An emergency service, such as a fire station or ER.

BackgroundNewsArticle.name: BackgroundNewsArticle
BackgroundNewsArticle.help: A [[NewsArticle]] providing historical context, definition and detail on a specific topic (aka "explainer" or "backgrounder"). For example, an in-depth article or frequently-asked-questions ([FAQ](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FAQ)) document on topics such as Climate Change or the European Union. Other kinds of background material from a non-news setting are often described using [[Book]] or [[Article]], in particular [[ScholarlyArticle]]. See also [[NewsArticle]] for related vocabulary from a learning/education perspective.

Course.name: Course
Course.help: A description of an educational course which may be offered as distinct instances at which take place at different times or take place at different locations, or be offered through different media or modes of study. An educational course is a sequence of one or more educational events and/or creative works which aims to build knowledge, competence or ability of learners.

inputs.name: courseCode
inputs.help: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

inputs.name: coursePrerequisites
inputs.help: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using [[AlignmentObject]].

inputs.name: educationalCredentialAwarded
inputs.help: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

inputs.name: hasCourseInstance
inputs.help: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

inputs.name: numberOfCredits
inputs.help: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

inputs.name: occupationalCredentialAwarded
inputs.help: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

HowTo.name: HowTo
HowTo.help: Instructions that explain how to achieve a result by performing a sequence of steps.

inputs.name: estimatedCost
inputs.help: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

inputs.name: performTime
inputs.help: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: prepTime
inputs.help: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: step
inputs.help: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

inputs.name: steps
inputs.help: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

inputs.name: supply
inputs.help: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

inputs.name: tool
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

inputs.name: totalTime
inputs.help: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: yield
inputs.help: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.

MusicReleaseFormatType.name: MusicReleaseFormatType
MusicReleaseFormatType.help: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

HowToDirection.name: HowToDirection
HowToDirection.help: A direction indicating a single action to do in the instructions for how to achieve a result.

inputs.name: afterMedia
inputs.help: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

inputs.name: beforeMedia
inputs.help: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

inputs.name: duringMedia
inputs.help: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

inputs.name: performTime
inputs.help: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: prepTime
inputs.help: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: supply
inputs.help: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

inputs.name: tool
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

inputs.name: totalTime
inputs.help: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: addressCountry
inputs.help: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1).

inputs.name: addressLocality
inputs.help: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

inputs.name: addressRegion
inputs.help: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country)

inputs.name: postOfficeBoxNumber
inputs.help: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

inputs.name: postalCode
inputs.help: The postal code. For example, 94043.

inputs.name: streetAddress
inputs.help: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

ItemListOrderType.name: ItemListOrderType
ItemListOrderType.help: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.

UserBlocks.name: UserBlocks
UserBlocks.help: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

AuthorizeAction.name: AuthorizeAction
AuthorizeAction.help: The act of granting permission to an object.

inputs.name: recipient
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

PaymentMethod.name: PaymentMethod
