A [[Guide]] may represent a Ranked List and recommend specific products or services with ranking.

inputs.name: reviewAspect
inputs.help: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

AddAction.name: AddAction
AddAction.help: The act of editing by adding an object to a collection.

BoatTerminal.name: BoatTerminal
BoatTerminal.help: A terminal for boats, ships, and other water vessels.

MedicalProcedure.name: MedicalProcedure
MedicalProcedure.help: A process of care used in either a diagnostic, therapeutic, preventive or palliative capacity that relies on invasive (surgical), non-invasive, or other techniques.

inputs.name: bodyLocation
inputs.help: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

inputs.name: followup
inputs.help: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

inputs.name: howPerformed
inputs.help: How the procedure is performed.

inputs.name: preparation
inputs.help: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

inputs.name: procedureType
inputs.help: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

inputs.name: status
inputs.help: The status of the study (enumerated).

inputs.name: hasDigitalDocumentPermission
inputs.help: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to "public".

Intangible.name: Intangible
Intangible.help: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

MedicalGuideline.name: MedicalGuideline
MedicalGuideline.help: Any recommendation made by a standard society (e.g. ACC/AHA) or consensus statement that denotes how to diagnose and treat a particular condition. Note: this type should be used to tag the actual guideline recommendation; if the guideline recommendation occurs in a larger scholarly article, use MedicalScholarlyArticle to tag the overall article, not this type. Note also: the organization making the recommendation should be captured in the recognizingAuthority base property of MedicalEntity.

inputs.name: evidenceLevel
inputs.help: Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).

inputs.name: evidenceOrigin
inputs.help: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

inputs.name: guidelineDate
inputs.help: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

inputs.name: guidelineSubject
inputs.help: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

inputs.name: caption
inputs.help: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the [[encodingFormat]].

inputs.name: embeddedTextCaption
inputs.help: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

inputs.name: transcript
inputs.help: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

IndividualProduct.name: IndividualProduct
IndividualProduct.help: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).

inputs.name: serialNumber
inputs.help: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

MotorizedBicycle.name: MotorizedBicycle
MotorizedBicycle.help: A motorized bicycle is a bicycle with an attached motor used to power the vehicle, or to assist with pedaling.

ItemAvailability.name: ItemAvailability
ItemAvailability.help: A list of possible product availability options.

SocialMediaPosting.name: SocialMediaPosting
SocialMediaPosting.help: A post to a social media platform, including blog posts, tweets, Facebook posts, etc.

inputs.name: sharedContent
inputs.help: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

AggregateOffer.name: AggregateOffer
AggregateOffer.help: When a single product is associated with multiple offers (for example, the same pair of shoes is offered by different merchants), then AggregateOffer can be used.\n\nNote: AggregateOffers are normally expected to associate multiple offers that all share the same defined [[businessFunction]] value, or default to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell if businessFunction is not explicitly defined.

inputs.name: highPrice
inputs.help:
The highest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

inputs.name: lowPrice
inputs.help:
The lowest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

inputs.name: offerCount
inputs.help: The number of offers for the product.

inputs.name: offers
inputs.help: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

Poster.name: Poster
Poster.help: A large, usually printed placard, bill, or announcement, often illustrated, that is posted to advertise or publicize something.

CourseInstance.name: CourseInstance
CourseInstance.help: An instance of a [[Course]] which is distinct from other instances because it is offered at a different time or location or through different media or modes of study or to a specific section of students.

inputs.name: courseMode
inputs.help: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

inputs.name: courseWorkload
inputs.help: The amount of work expected of students taking the course, often provided as a figure per week or per month, and may be broken down by type. For example, "2 hours of lectures, 1 hour of lab work and 3 hours of independent study per week".

inputs.name: instructor
inputs.help: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the [[CourseInstance]].

inputs.name: assesses
inputs.help: The item being described is intended to assess the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

inputs.name: educationalLevel
inputs.help: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

inputs.name: teaches
inputs.help: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

BedType.name: BedType
BedType.help: A type of bed. This is used for indicating the bed or beds available in an accommodation.

CovidTestingFacility.name: CovidTestingFacility
CovidTestingFacility.help:
A CovidTestingFacility is a [[MedicalClinic]] where testing for the COVID-19 Coronavirus
      disease is available. If the facility is being made available from an established [[Pharmacy]], [[Hotel]], or other
      non-medical organization, multiple types can be listed. This makes it easier to re-use existing schema.org information
      about that place e.g. contact info, address, opening hours. Note that in an emergency, such information may not always be reliable.

SizeSystemEnumeration.name: SizeSystemEnumeration
SizeSystemEnumeration.help: Enumerates common size systems for different categories of products, for example "EN-13402" or "UK" for wearables or "Imperial" for screws.

PodcastSeason.name: PodcastSeason
PodcastSeason.help: A single season of a podcast. Many podcasts do not break down into separate seasons. In that case, PodcastSeries should be used.

MedicalObservationalStudyDesign.name: MedicalObservationalStudyDesign
MedicalObservationalStudyDesign.help: Design models for observational medical studies. Enumerated type.

CDCPMDRecord.name: CDCPMDRecord
CDCPMDRecord.help:
A CDCPMDRecord is a data structure representing a record in a CDC tabular data format
      used for hospital data reporting. See [documentation](/docs/cdc-covid.html) for details, and the linked CDC materials for authoritative
      definitions used as the source here.

inputs.name: cvdCollectionDate
inputs.help: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

inputs.name: cvdFacilityCounty
inputs.help: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

inputs.name: cvdFacilityId
inputs.help: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

inputs.name: cvdNumBeds
inputs.help: numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

inputs.name: cvdNumBedsOcc
inputs.help: numbedsocc - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient beds that are occupied.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19Died
inputs.help: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19HOPats
inputs.help: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19HospPats
inputs.help: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19MechVentPats
inputs.help: numc19mechventpats - HOSPITALIZED and VENTILATED: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19 and are on a mechanical ventilator.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats
inputs.help: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

inputs.name: cvdNumC19OverflowPats
inputs.help: numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

inputs.name: cvdNumICUBeds
inputs.help: numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

inputs.name: cvdNumICUBedsOcc
inputs.help: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

inputs.name: cvdNumTotBeds
inputs.help: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all Inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed,ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

inputs.name: cvdNumVent
inputs.help: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

inputs.name: cvdNumVentUse
inputs.help: numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

inputs.name: datePosted
inputs.help: Publication date of an online listing.

HobbyShop.name: HobbyShop
HobbyShop.help: A store that sells materials useful or necessary for various hobbies.

PaintAction.name: PaintAction
PaintAction.help: The act of producing a painting, typically with paint and canvas as instruments.

Review.name: Review
Review.help: A review of an item - for example, of a restaurant, movie, or store.

inputs.name: associatedClaimReview
inputs.help: An associated [[ClaimReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

inputs.name: associatedMediaReview
inputs.help: An associated [[MediaReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

inputs.name: associatedReview
inputs.help: An associated [[Review]].

inputs.name: itemReviewed
inputs.help: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

inputs.name: negativeNotes
inputs.help: Indicates, in the context of a [[Review]] (e.g. framed as 'pro' vs 'con' considerations), negative considerations - either as unstructured text, or a list.

inputs.name: positiveNotes
inputs.help: Indicates, in the context of a [[Review]] (e.g. framed as 'pro' vs 'con' considerations), positive considerations - either as unstructured text, or a list.

inputs.name: reviewAspect
inputs.help: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

inputs.name: reviewBody
inputs.help: The actual body of the review.

inputs.name: reviewRating
inputs.help: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The ```reviewRating``` applies to rating given by the review. The [[aggregateRating]] property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

ReportedDoseSchedule.name: ReportedDoseSchedule
ReportedDoseSchedule.help: A patient-reported or observed dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

MusicAlbumReleaseType.name: MusicAlbumReleaseType
MusicAlbumReleaseType.help: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

inputs.name: defaultValue
inputs.help: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

inputs.name: maxValue
inputs.help: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: minValue
inputs.help: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

inputs.name: multipleValues
inputs.help: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

inputs.name: readonlyValue
inputs.help: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

inputs.name: stepValue
inputs.help: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

inputs.name: valueMaxLength
inputs.help: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

inputs.name: valueMinLength
inputs.help: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

inputs.name: valueName
inputs.help: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

inputs.name: valuePattern
inputs.help: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

inputs.name: valueRequired
inputs.help: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

Language.name: Language
Language.help: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in [BCP 47](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IETF_language_tag) can be used via the [[alternateName]] property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using [[ComputerLanguage]].

ReactAction.name: ReactAction
ReactAction.help: The act of responding instinctively and emotionally to an object, expressing a sentiment.

AccountingService.name: AccountingService
AccountingService.help: Accountancy business.\n\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

ExchangeRateSpecification.name: ExchangeRateSpecification
ExchangeRateSpecification.help: A structured value representing exchange rate.

inputs.name: currency
inputs.help: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: currentExchangeRate
inputs.help: The current price of a currency.

inputs.name: exchangeRateSpread
inputs.help: The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.

ComputerLanguage.name: ComputerLanguage
ComputerLanguage.help: This type covers computer programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, as well as other language-like computer representations. Natural languages are best represented with the [[Language]] type.

DepartAction.name: DepartAction
DepartAction.help: The act of  departing from a place. An agent departs from an fromLocation for a destination, optionally with participants.

WebSite.name: WebSite
WebSite.help: A WebSite is a set of related web pages and other items typically served from a single web domain and accessible via URLs.

inputs.name: issn
inputs.help: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

ShippingRateSettings.name: ShippingRateSettings
ShippingRateSettings.help: A ShippingRateSettings represents re-usable pieces of shipping information. It is designed for publication on an URL that may be referenced via the [[shippingSettingsLink]] property of an [[OfferShippingDetails]]. Several occurrences can be published, distinguished and matched (i.e. identified/referenced) by their different values for [[shippingLabel]].

inputs.name: doesNotShip
inputs.help: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

inputs.name: freeShippingThreshold
inputs.help: A monetary value above which (or equal to) the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

inputs.name: isUnlabelledFallback
inputs.help: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

inputs.name: shippingDestination
inputs.help: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways e.g. postalCode ranges.

inputs.name: shippingLabel
inputs.help: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[ShippingRateSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

inputs.name: shippingRate
inputs.help: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

inputs.name: endorsee
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

WPFooter.name: WPFooter
WPFooter.help: The footer section of the page.

Patient.name: Patient
Patient.help: A patient is any person recipient of health care services.

inputs.name: diagnosis
inputs.help: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

inputs.name: drug
inputs.help: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

inputs.name: healthCondition
inputs.help: Specifying the health condition(s) of a patient, medical study, or other target audience.

FMRadioChannel.name: FMRadioChannel
FMRadioChannel.help: A radio channel that uses FM.

InvestmentOrDeposit.name: InvestmentOrDeposit
InvestmentOrDeposit.help: A type of financial product that typically requires the client to transfer funds to a financial service in return for potential beneficial financial return.

inputs.name: amount
inputs.help: The amount of money.

DanceGroup.name: DanceGroup
DanceGroup.help: A dance group—for example, the Alvin Ailey Dance Theater or Riverdance.

MedicalDevice.name: MedicalDevice
MedicalDevice.help: Any object used in a medical capacity, such as to diagnose or treat a patient.

inputs.name: adverseOutcome
inputs.help: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or is otherwise life-threatening or requires immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriouseAdverseOutcome instead.

inputs.name: contraindication
inputs.help: A contraindication for this therapy.

inputs.name: postOp
inputs.help: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

inputs.name: preOp
inputs.help: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

inputs.name: procedure
inputs.help: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

inputs.name: seriousAdverseOutcome
inputs.help: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

DDxElement.name: DDxElement
DDxElement.help: An alternative, closely-related condition typically considered later in the differential diagnosis process along with the signs that are used to distinguish it.

inputs.name: diagnosis
inputs.help: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

inputs.name: distinguishingSign
inputs.help: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

FloorPlan.name: FloorPlan
FloorPlan.help: A FloorPlan is an explicit representation of a collection of similar accommodations, allowing the provision of common information (room counts, sizes, layout diagrams) and offers for rental or sale. In typical use, some [[ApartmentComplex]] has an [[accommodationFloorPlan]] which is a [[FloorPlan]].  A FloorPlan is always in the context of a particular place, either a larger [[ApartmentComplex]] or a single [[Apartment]]. The visual/spatial aspects of a floor plan (i.e. room layout, [see wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Floor_plan)) can be indicated using [[image]].

inputs.name: amenityFeature
inputs.help: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

inputs.name: floorSize
inputs.help:
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.
Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard

inputs.name: isPlanForApartment
inputs.help: Indicates some accommodation that this floor plan describes.

inputs.name: layoutImage
inputs.help: A schematic image showing the floorplan layout.

inputs.name: numberOfAccommodationUnits
inputs.help: Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits]].

inputs.name: numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits
inputs.help: Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAccommodationUnits]].

inputs.name: numberOfBathroomsTotal
inputs.help: The total integer number of bathrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions as [documented in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsTotalInteger+Field): "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also [[numberOfRooms]].

inputs.name: numberOfBedrooms
inputs.help: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

inputs.name: numberOfFullBathrooms
inputs.help: Number of full bathrooms - The total number of full and ¾ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsFull field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsFull+Field).

inputs.name: numberOfPartialBathrooms
inputs.help: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and ¼ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

inputs.name: numberOfRooms
inputs.help:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

inputs.name: petsAllowed
inputs.help: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

InviteAction.name: InviteAction
InviteAction.help: The act of asking someone to attend an event. Reciprocal of RsvpAction.

inputs.name: event
inputs.help: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

EmployeeRole.name: EmployeeRole
EmployeeRole.help: A subclass of OrganizationRole used to describe employee relationships.

inputs.name: baseSalary
inputs.help: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

inputs.name: salaryCurrency
inputs.help: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) ) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

HealthPlanCostSharingSpecification.name: HealthPlanCostSharingSpecification
HealthPlanCostSharingSpecification.help: A description of costs to the patient under a given network or formulary.

inputs.name: healthPlanCoinsuranceOption
inputs.help: Whether the coinsurance applies before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

inputs.name: healthPlanCoinsuranceRate
inputs.help: Whether The rate of coinsurance expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.

inputs.name: healthPlanCopay
inputs.help: Whether The copay amount.

inputs.name: healthPlanCopayOption
inputs.help: Whether the copay is before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

inputs.name: healthPlanPharmacyCategory
inputs.help: The category or type of pharmacy associated with this cost sharing.

MerchantReturnPolicySeasonalOverride.name: MerchantReturnPolicySeasonalOverride
MerchantReturnPolicySeasonalOverride.help: A seasonal override of a return policy, for example used for holidays.

inputs.name: endDate
inputs.help: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

inputs.name: merchantReturnDays
inputs.help: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

inputs.name: returnPolicyCategory
inputs.help: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

inputs.name: startDate
inputs.help: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

HomeAndConstructionBusiness.name: HomeAndConstructionBusiness
HomeAndConstructionBusiness.help:
A construction business.

A HomeAndConstructionBusiness is a [[LocalBusiness]] that provides services around homes and buildings.

As a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

DeleteAction.name: DeleteAction
DeleteAction.help: The act of editing a recipient by removing one of its objects.

Attorney.name: Attorney
Attorney.help: Professional service: Attorney. \n\nThis type is deprecated - [[LegalService]] is more inclusive and less ambiguous.

ReceiveAction.name: ReceiveAction
ReceiveAction.help:
The act of physically/electronically taking delivery of an object that has been transferred from an origin to a destination. Reciprocal of SendAction.

Related actions:

* [[SendAction]]: The reciprocal of ReceiveAction.
* [[TakeAction]]: Unlike TakeAction, ReceiveAction does not imply that the ownership has been transfered (e.g. I can receive a package, but it does not mean the package is now mine).

inputs.name: deliveryMethod
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

inputs.name: sender
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

MovieSeries.name: MovieSeries
MovieSeries.help: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.

inputs.name: actor
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: actors
inputs.help: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: director
inputs.help: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: directors
inputs.help: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

inputs.name: musicBy
inputs.help: The composer of the soundtrack.

inputs.name: productionCompany
inputs.help: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

inputs.name: trailer
inputs.help: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.

LodgingReservation.name: LodgingReservation
LodgingReservation.help: A reservation for lodging at a hotel, motel, inn, etc.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

inputs.name: checkinTime
inputs.help: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

inputs.name: checkoutTime
inputs.help: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

inputs.name: lodgingUnitDescription
inputs.help: A full description of the lodging unit.

inputs.name: lodgingUnitType
inputs.help: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

inputs.name: numAdults
inputs.help: The number of adults staying in the unit.

inputs.name: numChildren
inputs.help: The number of children staying in the unit.

Invoice.name: Invoice
Invoice.help: A statement of the money due for goods or services; a bill.

inputs.name: accountId
inputs.help: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

inputs.name: billingPeriod
inputs.help: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

inputs.name: broker
inputs.help: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

inputs.name: category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: confirmationNumber
inputs.help: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

inputs.name: customer
inputs.help: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

inputs.name: minimumPaymentDue
inputs.help: The minimum payment required at this time.

inputs.name: paymentDue
inputs.help: The date that payment is due.

inputs.name: paymentDueDate
inputs.help: The date that payment is due.

inputs.name: paymentMethod
inputs.help: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

inputs.name: paymentMethodId
inputs.help: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

inputs.name: paymentStatus
inputs.help: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

inputs.name: provider
inputs.help: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

inputs.name: referencesOrder
inputs.help: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

inputs.name: scheduledPaymentDate
inputs.help: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

inputs.name: totalPaymentDue
inputs.help: The total amount due.

ReservationPackage.name: ReservationPackage
ReservationPackage.help: A group of multiple reservations with common values for all sub-reservations.

inputs.name: subReservation
inputs.help: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

GeoCircle.name: GeoCircle
GeoCircle.help:
A GeoCircle is a GeoShape representing a circular geographic area. As it is a GeoShape
          it provides the simple textual property 'circle', but also allows the combination of postalCode alongside geoRadius.
          The center of the circle can be indicated via the 'geoMidpoint' property, or more approximately using 'address', 'postalCode'.

inputs.name: geoMidpoint
inputs.help: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape e.g. GeoCircle.

inputs.name: geoRadius
inputs.help: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

Consortium.name: Consortium
Consortium.help: A Consortium is a membership [[Organization]] whose members are typically Organizations.

WarrantyPromise.name: WarrantyPromise
WarrantyPromise.help: A structured value representing the duration and scope of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

inputs.name: durationOfWarranty
inputs.help: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

inputs.name: warrantyScope
inputs.help: The scope of the warranty promise.

GeoShape.name: GeoShape
GeoShape.help: The geographic shape of a place. A GeoShape can be described using several properties whose values are based on latitude/longitude pairs. Either whitespace or commas can be used to separate latitude and longitude; whitespace should be used when writing a list of several such points.

inputs.name: address
inputs.help: Physical address of the item.

inputs.name: addressCountry
inputs.help: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1).

inputs.name: box
inputs.help: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

inputs.name: circle
inputs.help: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

inputs.name: elevation
inputs.help: The elevation of a location ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT_OF_MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

inputs.name: line
inputs.help: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

inputs.name: polygon
inputs.help: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

inputs.name: postalCode
inputs.help: The postal code. For example, 94043.

DoseSchedule.name: DoseSchedule
DoseSchedule.help: A specific dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

inputs.name: doseUnit
inputs.help: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

inputs.name: doseValue
inputs.help: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

inputs.name: frequency
inputs.help: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

inputs.name: targetPopulation
inputs.help: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

BrokerageAccount.name: BrokerageAccount
BrokerageAccount.help: An account that allows an investor to deposit funds and place investment orders with a licensed broker or brokerage firm.

PublicationIssue.name: PublicationIssue
PublicationIssue.help: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.\n\nSee also [blog post](http://blog.schema.org/2014/09/schemaorg-support-for-bibliographic_2.html).

inputs.name: issueNumber
inputs.help: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

inputs.name: pageEnd
inputs.help: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

inputs.name: pageStart
inputs.help: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

inputs.name: pagination
inputs.help: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

LoseAction.name: LoseAction
LoseAction.help: The act of being defeated in a competitive activity.

inputs.name: winner
inputs.help: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

Comment.name: Comment
Comment.help: A comment on an item - for example, a comment on a blog post. The comment's content is expressed via the [[text]] property, and its topic via [[about]], properties shared with all CreativeWorks.

inputs.name: downvoteCount
inputs.help: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

inputs.name: parentItem
inputs.help: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

inputs.name: upvoteCount
inputs.help: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

AnatomicalSystem.name: AnatomicalSystem
AnatomicalSystem.help: An anatomical system is a group of anatomical structures that work together to perform a certain task. Anatomical systems, such as organ systems, are one organizing principle of anatomy, and can includes circulatory, digestive, endocrine, integumentary, immune, lymphatic, muscular, nervous, reproductive, respiratory, skeletal, urinary, vestibular, and other systems.

inputs.name: associatedPathophysiology
inputs.help: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

inputs.name: comprisedOf
inputs.help: Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

inputs.name: relatedCondition
inputs.help: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

inputs.name: relatedStructure
inputs.help: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

inputs.name: relatedTherapy
inputs.help: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

IgnoreAction.name: IgnoreAction
IgnoreAction.help: The act of intentionally disregarding the object. An agent ignores an object.

OfferCatalog.name: OfferCatalog
OfferCatalog.help: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.

SubscribeAction.name: SubscribeAction
SubscribeAction.help:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates pushed to.

Related actions:

* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, SubscribeAction implies that the subscriber acts as a passive agent being constantly/actively pushed for updates.
* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.

PathologyTest.name: PathologyTest
PathologyTest.help: A medical test performed by a laboratory that typically involves examination of a tissue sample by a pathologist.

inputs.name: tissueSample
inputs.help: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

BodyOfWater.name: BodyOfWater
BodyOfWater.help: A body of water, such as a sea, ocean, or lake.

Mountain.name: Mountain
Mountain.help: A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest.

APIReference.name: APIReference
APIReference.help: Reference documentation for application programming interfaces (APIs).

inputs.name: assembly
inputs.help: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

inputs.name: assemblyVersion
inputs.help: Associated product/technology version. e.g., .NET Framework 4.5.

inputs.name: executableLibraryName
inputs.help: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

inputs.name: programmingModel
inputs.help: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

inputs.name: targetPlatform
inputs.help: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

Diet.name: Diet
Diet.help: A strategy of regulating the intake of food to achieve or maintain a specific health-related goal.

inputs.name: dietFeatures
inputs.help: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

inputs.name: endorsers
inputs.help: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

inputs.name: expertConsiderations
inputs.help: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

inputs.name: physiologicalBenefits
inputs.help: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

inputs.name: risks
inputs.help: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

CableOrSatelliteService.name: CableOrSatelliteService
CableOrSatelliteService.help: A service which provides access to media programming like TV or radio. Access may be via cable or satellite.

MedicalCondition.name: MedicalCondition
MedicalCondition.help: Any condition of the human body that affects the normal functioning of a person, whether physically or mentally. Includes diseases, injuries, disabilities, disorders, syndromes, etc.

inputs.name: associatedAnatomy
inputs.help: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

inputs.name: differentialDiagnosis
inputs.help: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

inputs.name: drug
inputs.help: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

inputs.name: epidemiology
inputs.help: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

inputs.name: expectedPrognosis
inputs.help: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

inputs.name: naturalProgression
inputs.help: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

inputs.name: pathophysiology
inputs.help: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

inputs.name: possibleComplication
inputs.help: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

inputs.name: possibleTreatment
inputs.help: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

inputs.name: primaryPrevention
inputs.help: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

inputs.name: riskFactor
inputs.help: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

inputs.name: secondaryPrevention
inputs.help: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

inputs.name: signOrSymptom
inputs.help: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

inputs.name: stage
inputs.help: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

inputs.name: status
inputs.help: The status of the study (enumerated).

inputs.name: typicalTest
inputs.help: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

Offer.name: Offer
Offer.help:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service — for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

Note: As the [[businessFunction]] property, which identifies the form of offer (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose), defaults to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell; an Offer without a defined businessFunction value can be assumed to be an offer to sell.

For [GTIN](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin)-related fields, see [Check Digit calculator](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/support/check_digit_calculator) and [validation guide](http://www.gs1us.org/resources/standards/gtin-validation-guide) from [GS1](http://www.gs1.org/).

inputs.name: acceptedPaymentMethod
inputs.help: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

inputs.name: addOn
inputs.help: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

inputs.name: advanceBookingRequirement
inputs.help: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: areaServed
inputs.help: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

inputs.name: availability
inputs.help: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

inputs.name: availabilityEnds
inputs.help: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

inputs.name: availabilityStarts
inputs.help: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

inputs.name: availableAtOrFrom
inputs.help: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

inputs.name: availableDeliveryMethod
inputs.help: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

inputs.name: businessFunction
inputs.help: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

inputs.name: category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: deliveryLeadTime
inputs.help: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

inputs.name: eligibleCustomerType
inputs.help: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

inputs.name: eligibleDuration
inputs.help: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

inputs.name: eligibleQuantity
inputs.help: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

inputs.name: eligibleRegion
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: eligibleTransactionVolume
inputs.help: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

inputs.name: gtin
inputs.help: A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties. The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) express GTINs as URLs. A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged.

inputs.name: gtin12
inputs.help: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin13
inputs.help: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin14
inputs.help: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: gtin8
inputs.help: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

inputs.name: hasMeasurement
inputs.help: A product measurement, for example the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, or the gauge of a screw. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

inputs.name: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
inputs.help: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

inputs.name: includesObject
inputs.help: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

inputs.name: ineligibleRegion
inputs.help: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

inputs.name: inventoryLevel
inputs.help: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

inputs.name: itemCondition
inputs.help: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

inputs.name: itemOffered
inputs.help: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: leaseLength
inputs.help: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

inputs.name: mpn
inputs.help: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: offeredBy
inputs.help: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

inputs.name: price
inputs.help:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

inputs.name: priceCurrency
inputs.help: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

inputs.name: priceSpecification
inputs.help: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

inputs.name: priceValidUntil
inputs.help: The date after which the price is no longer available.

inputs.name: review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: reviews
inputs.help: Review of the item.

inputs.name: seller
inputs.help: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

inputs.name: serialNumber
inputs.help: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

inputs.name: shippingDetails
inputs.help: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

inputs.name: sku
inputs.help: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validThrough
inputs.help: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

inputs.name: warranty
inputs.help: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

inputs.name: foodEstablishment
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

inputs.name: foodEvent
inputs.help: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

inputs.name: recipe
inputs.help: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

Recipe.name: Recipe
Recipe.help: A recipe. For dietary restrictions covered by the recipe, a few common restrictions are enumerated via [[suitableForDiet]]. The [[keywords]] property can also be used to add more detail.

inputs.name: cookTime
inputs.help: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

inputs.name: cookingMethod
inputs.help: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

inputs.name: ingredients
inputs.help: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

inputs.name: nutrition
inputs.help: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

inputs.name: recipeCategory
inputs.help: The category of the recipe—for example, appetizer, entree, etc.

inputs.name: recipeCuisine
inputs.help: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

inputs.name: recipeIngredient
inputs.help: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

inputs.name: recipeInstructions
inputs.help: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

inputs.name: recipeYield
inputs.help: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

inputs.name: suitableForDiet
inputs.help: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

AllocateAction.name: AllocateAction
AllocateAction.help: The act of organizing tasks/objects/events by associating resources to it.

MedicalGuidelineContraindication.name: MedicalGuidelineContraindication
MedicalGuidelineContraindication.help: A guideline contraindication that designates a process as harmful and where quality of the data supporting the contraindication is sound.

Menu.name: Menu
Menu.help: A structured representation of food or drink items available from a FoodEstablishment.

inputs.name: hasMenuItem
inputs.help: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.

inputs.name: hasMenuSection
inputs.help: A subgrouping of the menu (by dishes, course, serving time period, etc.).

ParentAudience.name: ParentAudience
ParentAudience.help: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content.

inputs.name: childMaxAge
inputs.help: Maximal age of the child.

inputs.name: childMinAge
inputs.help: Minimal age of the child.

Dataset.name: Dataset
Dataset.help: A body of structured information describing some topic(s) of interest.

inputs.name: catalog
inputs.help: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

inputs.name: datasetTimeInterval
inputs.help: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

inputs.name: distribution
inputs.help: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.

inputs.name: includedDataCatalog
inputs.help: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

inputs.name: includedInDataCatalog
inputs.help: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

inputs.name: issn
inputs.help: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

inputs.name: measurementTechnique
inputs.help:
A technique or technology used in a [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]),
corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using [[variableMeasured]]). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]].

inputs.name: resultOf
inputs.help: Inverse of property result

inputs.name: variableMeasured
inputs.help: The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue.

RadioSeason.name: RadioSeason
RadioSeason.help: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

NLNonprofitType.name: NLNonprofitType
NLNonprofitType.help: NLNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the Netherlands.

DrugStrength.name: DrugStrength
DrugStrength.help: A specific strength in which a medical drug is available in a specific country.

inputs.name: activeIngredient
inputs.help: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

inputs.name: availableIn
inputs.help: The location in which the strength is available.

inputs.name: maximumIntake
inputs.help: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

inputs.name: strengthUnit
inputs.help: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

inputs.name: strengthValue
inputs.help: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

CheckInAction.name: CheckInAction
CheckInAction.help:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their arrival by registering/confirming for a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check in) or at a place (e.g. hotel), possibly resulting in a result (boarding pass, etc).

Related actions:

* [[CheckOutAction]]: The antonym of CheckInAction.
* [[ArriveAction]]: Unlike ArriveAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the start of a previously reserved service.
* [[ConfirmAction]]: Unlike ConfirmAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the *start* of a previously reserved service rather than its validity/existence.

MedicalClinic.name: MedicalClinic
MedicalClinic.help: A facility, often associated with a hospital or medical school, that is devoted to the specific diagnosis and/or healthcare. Previously limited to outpatients but with evolution it may be open to inpatients as well.

inputs.name: availableService
inputs.help: A medical service available from this provider.

inputs.name: medicalSpecialty
inputs.help: A medical specialty of the provider.

Artery.name: Artery
Artery.help: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood away from the heart.

inputs.name: arterialBranch
inputs.help: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

inputs.name: supplyTo
inputs.help: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

InteractAction.name: InteractAction
InteractAction.help: The act of interacting with another person or organization.

Conversation.name: Conversation
Conversation.help: One or more messages between organizations or people on a particular topic. Individual messages can be linked to the conversation with isPartOf or hasPart properties.

InvestmentFund.name: InvestmentFund
InvestmentFund.help: A company or fund that gathers capital from a number of investors to create a pool of money that is then re-invested into stocks, bonds and other assets.

AdvertiserContentArticle.name: AdvertiserContentArticle
AdvertiserContentArticle.help: An [[Article]] that an external entity has paid to place or to produce to its specifications. Includes [advertorials](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advertorial), sponsored content, native advertising and other paid content.

Answer.name: Answer
Answer.help: An answer offered to a question; perhaps correct, perhaps opinionated or wrong.

inputs.name: answerExplanation
inputs.help: A step-by-step or full explanation about Answer. Can outline how this Answer was achieved or contain more broad clarification or statement about it.

MedicalEvidenceLevel.name: MedicalEvidenceLevel
MedicalEvidenceLevel.help: Level of evidence for a medical guideline. Enumerated type.

DietarySupplement.name: DietarySupplement
DietarySupplement.help: A product taken by mouth that contains a dietary ingredient intended to supplement the diet. Dietary ingredients may include vitamins, minerals, herbs or other botanicals, amino acids, and substances such as enzymes, organ tissues, glandulars and metabolites.

inputs.name: activeIngredient
inputs.help: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

inputs.name: isProprietary
inputs.help: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

inputs.name: legalStatus
inputs.help: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

inputs.name: manufacturer
inputs.help: The manufacturer of the product.

inputs.name: maximumIntake
inputs.help: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

inputs.name: mechanismOfAction
inputs.help: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

inputs.name: nonProprietaryName
inputs.help: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

inputs.name: proprietaryName
inputs.help: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

inputs.name: recommendedIntake
inputs.help: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

inputs.name: safetyConsideration
inputs.help: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

inputs.name: targetPopulation
inputs.help: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

Role.name: Role
Role.help: Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.\n\nSee also [blog post](http://blog.schema.org/2014/06/introducing-role.html).

inputs.name: endDate
inputs.help: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

inputs.name: namedPosition
inputs.help: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

inputs.name: roleName
inputs.help: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

inputs.name: startDate
inputs.help: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

TechArticle.name: TechArticle
TechArticle.help: A technical article - Example: How-to (task) topics, step-by-step, procedural troubleshooting, specifications, etc.

inputs.name: dependencies
inputs.help: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

inputs.name: proficiencyLevel
inputs.help: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

inputs.name: tickerSymbol
inputs.help: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO15022.

BroadcastEvent.name: BroadcastEvent
BroadcastEvent.help: An over the air or online broadcast event.

inputs.name: broadcastOfEvent
inputs.help: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

inputs.name: isLiveBroadcast
inputs.help: True if the broadcast is of a live event.

inputs.name: subtitleLanguage
inputs.help: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

inputs.name: videoFormat
inputs.help: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

Service.name: Service
Service.help: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

inputs.name: aggregateRating
inputs.help: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

inputs.name: areaServed
inputs.help: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

inputs.name: audience
inputs.help: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

inputs.name: availableChannel
inputs.help: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

inputs.name: award
inputs.help: An award won by or for this item.

inputs.name: brand
inputs.help: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

inputs.name: broker
inputs.help: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

inputs.name: category
inputs.help: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

inputs.name: hasOfferCatalog
inputs.help: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

inputs.name: hoursAvailable
inputs.help: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

inputs.name: isRelatedTo
inputs.help: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

inputs.name: isSimilarTo
inputs.help: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

inputs.name: logo
inputs.help: An associated logo.

inputs.name: offers
inputs.help: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

inputs.name: produces
inputs.help: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

inputs.name: provider
inputs.help: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

inputs.name: providerMobility
inputs.help: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

inputs.name: review
inputs.help: A review of the item.

inputs.name: serviceArea
inputs.help: The geographic area where the service is provided.

inputs.name: serviceAudience
inputs.help: The audience eligible for this service.

inputs.name: serviceOutput
inputs.help: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

inputs.name: serviceType
inputs.help: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

inputs.name: slogan
inputs.help: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

inputs.name: termsOfService
inputs.help: Human-readable terms of service documentation.

Canal.name: Canal
Canal.help: A canal, like the Panama Canal.

OpeningHoursSpecification.name: OpeningHoursSpecification
OpeningHoursSpecification.help:
A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.


The place is __open__ if the [[opens]] property is specified, and __closed__ otherwise.

If the value for the [[closes]] property is less than the value for the [[opens]] property then the hour range is assumed to span over the next day.

inputs.name: closes
inputs.help: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

inputs.name: dayOfWeek
inputs.help: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

inputs.name: opens
inputs.help: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

inputs.name: validFrom
inputs.help: The date when the item becomes valid.

inputs.name: validThrough
inputs.help: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

LinkRole.name: LinkRole
LinkRole.help: A Role that represents a Web link e.g. as expressed via the 'url' property. Its linkRelationship property can indicate URL-based and plain textual link types e.g. those in IANA link registry or others such as 'amphtml'. This structure provides a placeholder where details from HTML's link element can be represented outside of HTML, e.g. in JSON-LD feeds.

inputs.name: inLanguage
inputs.help: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

inputs.name: linkRelationship
inputs.help: Indicates the relationship type of a Web link.

InstallAction.name: InstallAction
InstallAction.help: The act of installing an application.

BuyAction.name: BuyAction
BuyAction.help: The act of giving money to a seller in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent buys an object, product, or service from a seller for a price. Reciprocal of SellAction.

inputs.name: seller
inputs.help: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

inputs.name: vendor
inputs.help: 'vendor' is an earlier term for 'seller'.

inputs.name: warrantyPromise
inputs.help: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

DriveWheelConfigurationValue.name: DriveWheelConfigurationValue
DriveWheelConfigurationValue.help: A value indicating which roadwheels will receive torque.

Bone.name: Bone
Bone.help: Rigid connective tissue that comprises up the skeletal structure of the human body.

SizeGroupEnumeration.name: SizeGroupEnumeration
SizeGroupEnumeration.help: Enumerates common size groups for various product categories.

ViewAction.name: ViewAction
ViewAction.help: The act of consuming static visual content.

DigitalDocumentPermission.name: DigitalDocumentPermission
DigitalDocumentPermission.help: A permission for a particular person or group to access a particular file.

inputs.name: grantee
inputs.help: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

inputs.name: permissionType
inputs.help: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

ClaimReview.name: ClaimReview
ClaimReview.help: A fact-checking review of claims made (or reported) in some creative work (referenced via itemReviewed).

inputs.name: claimReviewed
inputs.help: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

PerformanceRole.name: PerformanceRole
PerformanceRole.help: A PerformanceRole is a Role that some entity places with regard to a theatrical performance, e.g. in a Movie, TVSeries etc.

inputs.name: characterName
inputs.help: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

UnRegisterAction.name: UnRegisterAction
UnRegisterAction.help:
The act of un-registering from a service.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: antonym of UnRegisterAction.
* [[LeaveAction]]: Unlike LeaveAction, UnRegisterAction implies that you are unregistering from a service you werer previously registered, rather than leaving a team/group of people.

HealthTopicContent.name: HealthTopicContent
HealthTopicContent.help: [[HealthTopicContent]] is [[WebContent]] that is about some aspect of a health topic, e.g. a condition, its symptoms or treatments. Such content may be comprised of several parts or sections and use different types of media. Multiple instances of [[WebContent]] (and hence [[HealthTopicContent]]) can be related using [[hasPart]] / [[isPartOf]] where there is some kind of content hierarchy, and their content described with [[about]] and [[mentions]] e.g. building upon the existing [[MedicalCondition]] vocabulary.

inputs.name: hasHealthAspect
